1
00:00:54,708 --> 00:00:58,000
[voice panting heavily]

2
00:01:04,041 --> 00:01:05,500
[Charlie, in English] I hate running!

3
00:01:05,583 --> 00:01:08,000
[Rafa] So, you all dated one another?

4
00:01:08,083 --> 00:01:09,041
As in...

5
00:01:09,125 --> 00:01:10,958
[in Filipino]
All of you are each other's exes?

6
00:01:11,041 --> 00:01:12,416
Yeah.

7
00:01:12,500 --> 00:01:14,916
But not all of that was serious.

8
00:01:15,500 --> 00:01:17,375
Some were just hookups.

9
00:01:17,458 --> 00:01:20,208
Some were just for fun.

10
00:01:21,958 --> 00:01:24,250
[Rafa, in English] And you're
telling me about this just now?

11
00:01:24,333 --> 00:01:26,333
-[in Filipino] It's your turn here.
-[machine stops]

12
00:01:29,083 --> 00:01:31,875
[in English] And you're all still friends?

13
00:01:33,125 --> 00:01:35,416
[exhales] Best friends!

14
00:01:35,500 --> 00:01:37,166
[sarcastically] Best friends.

15
00:01:37,250 --> 00:01:39,333
Ride or die!

16
00:01:39,416 --> 00:01:40,541
Die!

17
00:01:41,125 --> 00:01:42,125
Huh?

18
00:01:42,208 --> 00:01:43,625
[Rafa] You have history.

19
00:01:43,708 --> 00:01:47,125
Something that you conveniently
failed to mention, Charlie.

20
00:01:47,208 --> 00:01:48,416
[in Filipino] You know...

21
00:01:49,458 --> 00:01:51,291
-[treadmill starts running]
-I think you'll like them.

22
00:01:51,875 --> 00:01:55,208
But for that to happen,
you need to meet them first.

23
00:01:55,958 --> 00:01:58,833
Do you want me to give you a rundown?

24
00:01:58,916 --> 00:02:00,125
[bright upbeat music playing]

25
00:02:00,208 --> 00:02:02,500
[Charlie] There are four of us
in the group.

26
00:02:03,458 --> 00:02:07,708
I'm the one who brings real talk
and tough love to our friendship.

27
00:02:08,458 --> 00:02:09,500
And then there's Hannah.

28
00:02:09,583 --> 00:02:12,791
She's the most caring, understanding

29
00:02:12,875 --> 00:02:13,875
and nurturing one in the group.

30
00:02:13,958 --> 00:02:16,000
Kind of like the mom.

31
00:02:16,083 --> 00:02:17,041
Then there's Mihan.

32
00:02:17,125 --> 00:02:18,666
She's a Virgo too, just like you!

33
00:02:18,750 --> 00:02:20,875
-She's always got a lot to say.
-[Rafa] Oh, really?

34
00:02:20,958 --> 00:02:23,541
[Charlie] She always wants the best
for everyone

35
00:02:23,625 --> 00:02:26,375
but... [chuckles] it always ends up
sounding like a boring lecture.

36
00:02:26,458 --> 00:02:27,875
And then there's Kit!

37
00:02:27,958 --> 00:02:31,000
[in English] She's the bestest friend
anyone could ever ask for.

38
00:02:31,083 --> 00:02:32,458
[in Filipino] 'Cause whether you're right
or wrong,

39
00:02:32,541 --> 00:02:33,916
she's always on your side.

40
00:02:34,833 --> 00:02:37,625
[Rafa] So seriously, how did you guys
even end up as exes?

41
00:02:37,708 --> 00:02:40,458
[Charlie] Okay, the super quick rundown.

42
00:02:40,958 --> 00:02:43,750
Back in high school, Kit and Mihan kissed

43
00:02:43,833 --> 00:02:46,333
because of
a "Seven minutes in heaven" dare.

44
00:02:46,416 --> 00:02:48,416
[bright upbeat music continues]

45
00:02:51,333 --> 00:02:52,500
Nothing followed.

46
00:02:55,708 --> 00:02:58,500
Hannah and I were college sweethearts.

47
00:02:58,583 --> 00:03:00,250
We were together for a year and a month.

48
00:03:00,333 --> 00:03:04,083
But when you're that young,
that feels like forever.

49
00:03:12,583 --> 00:03:16,500
Hannah and Mihan were
best friends turned lovers.

50
00:03:16,583 --> 00:03:17,958
It seemed perfect.

51
00:03:18,041 --> 00:03:19,541
Almost perfect.

52
00:03:19,625 --> 00:03:22,916
But their relationship ended
after five years.

53
00:03:29,333 --> 00:03:32,125
Hannah and Kit had a one-night stand.

54
00:03:32,208 --> 00:03:33,625
Hannah was just trying to shake things off

55
00:03:33,708 --> 00:03:35,166
after her breakup with Mihan.

56
00:03:35,250 --> 00:03:36,166
[shushing]

57
00:03:41,583 --> 00:03:43,625
As for Mihan and me...

58
00:03:43,708 --> 00:03:45,916
-[bell dings]
-It was just a situationship.

59
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:48,916
She ended up ghosting me.

60
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:50,625
[scoffs, in English] You still follow?

61
00:03:50,708 --> 00:03:51,541
[Rafa] Barely.

62
00:03:51,625 --> 00:03:54,500
Wait, by this time,
you were both Hannah's exes, right?

63
00:03:54,583 --> 00:03:57,250
[Charlie] See?! You can still follow.

64
00:03:57,333 --> 00:03:58,750
[in Filipino] Last one.

65
00:03:58,833 --> 00:04:01,125
-[phone notification chimes]
-Me and Kit were FUBUs.

66
00:04:01,208 --> 00:04:02,708
It was meant to be just for fun

67
00:04:02,791 --> 00:04:07,000
but I tried to get
a relationship out of it...

68
00:04:07,083 --> 00:04:09,083
and she's allergic to relationships.

69
00:04:11,500 --> 00:04:13,750
[woman 2, in English] I feel like
I need to write this down or something...

70
00:04:13,833 --> 00:04:15,125
[Charlie, in Filipino]
There's no need for that!

71
00:04:15,208 --> 00:04:17,375
All of these don't matter anymore

72
00:04:17,458 --> 00:04:19,791
because we're all best friends now.

73
00:04:25,208 --> 00:04:27,458
[woman 2, in English]
So, do you want to meet my exes?

74
00:04:28,583 --> 00:04:30,416
Well, are they your best friends?

75
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:31,625
[chuckles incredulously]

76
00:04:31,708 --> 00:04:34,750
[in Filipino]
You didn't have clean breakups.

77
00:04:34,833 --> 00:04:37,666
Someone ghosted, someone cheated.

78
00:04:37,750 --> 00:04:39,500
How did you all become best friends?

79
00:04:40,208 --> 00:04:41,083
Hmm.

80
00:04:41,833 --> 00:04:44,333
I know it's not easy to understand

81
00:04:45,208 --> 00:04:48,166
[in English] but, babe,
that's a good topic for later.

82
00:04:48,250 --> 00:04:49,333
Ask them!

83
00:04:52,041 --> 00:04:54,625
[in Filipino] You know, babe,
once you meet and spend time with them

84
00:04:54,708 --> 00:04:56,875
all your negative feelings will go away.

85
00:04:56,958 --> 00:04:59,750
You'll see that there's nothing
between us anymore.

86
00:04:59,833 --> 00:05:01,375
[in English]
You have nothing to worry about.

87
00:05:01,458 --> 00:05:03,458
Um, did I agree to come?

88
00:05:03,541 --> 00:05:04,416
Huh?

89
00:05:04,500 --> 00:05:06,666
Did I say that I'm okay with meeting them?

90
00:05:10,375 --> 00:05:12,500
[easygoing music playing]

91
00:05:24,083 --> 00:05:27,708
[phone rings]

92
00:05:33,458 --> 00:05:35,250
Hey, Charlie. Are you on your way?

93
00:05:35,333 --> 00:05:37,500
Is Rafa with you?

94
00:05:46,583 --> 00:05:48,958
Hey, Kit, you're leaving early?

95
00:05:50,583 --> 00:05:52,250
Um... [chuckles]

96
00:05:52,333 --> 00:05:53,250
I'm sorry. I have to go.

97
00:05:53,333 --> 00:05:55,250
Oh, but it's a Sunday, Kit.

98
00:05:55,333 --> 00:05:57,708
Stay a little longer, please?

99
00:05:57,791 --> 00:05:58,833
Um...

100
00:05:58,916 --> 00:06:02,083
[in English] I'm sorry,
but my Sundays are sacred.

101
00:06:03,583 --> 00:06:05,250
Church?

102
00:06:05,333 --> 00:06:07,208
Yeah, something like that.

103
00:06:07,833 --> 00:06:09,750
Sorry, but I really have to go.

104
00:06:09,833 --> 00:06:11,333
No.

105
00:06:12,333 --> 00:06:13,625
Okay, fine.

106
00:06:13,708 --> 00:06:15,333
But when will I see you again?

107
00:06:19,333 --> 00:06:21,625
Hey... Bye.

108
00:06:21,708 --> 00:06:23,708
[Mihan] Hmm...

109
00:06:25,708 --> 00:06:27,583
Okay, this is it.

110
00:06:31,750 --> 00:06:32,625
Mom?

111
00:06:33,833 --> 00:06:34,958
[in Filipino] Mom, I'm leaving now.

112
00:06:36,958 --> 00:06:39,250
[Mihan's mom] Please give this to Hannah.

113
00:06:39,333 --> 00:06:40,375
What are all these?

114
00:06:40,458 --> 00:06:42,375
Here are some essential oils.

115
00:06:42,458 --> 00:06:44,125
There's peppermint and lavender.

116
00:06:44,208 --> 00:06:45,500
I was chatting with her, and she mentioned

117
00:06:45,583 --> 00:06:47,125
that she still hasn't recovered
from her cold and her headache.

118
00:06:47,208 --> 00:06:48,125
And she still has a headache.

119
00:06:48,208 --> 00:06:49,333
-[in English] Okay, okay, thank you.
-[in Filipino] Goodness.

120
00:06:49,416 --> 00:06:52,750
Hannah takes care of all of you,

121
00:06:52,833 --> 00:06:54,750
but who takes care of her?

122
00:06:54,833 --> 00:06:56,208
Do you want to volunteer?

123
00:06:56,291 --> 00:06:58,125
I think you'd be a better fit.

124
00:06:58,208 --> 00:06:59,125
You're impossible, Mom.

125
00:06:59,208 --> 00:07:02,375
Oh, but wait. Please force her to take
sick leave this week.

126
00:07:02,458 --> 00:07:07,000
Otherwise, she won't recover
if she doesn't take a break.

127
00:07:07,083 --> 00:07:09,125
[in English] I'll try my best, okay?

128
00:07:09,208 --> 00:07:11,000
-I'll go ahead now.
-[doorbell rings]

129
00:07:11,083 --> 00:07:11,958
Are you expecting someone?

130
00:07:13,208 --> 00:07:14,166
[in Filipino] My suitor.

131
00:07:14,250 --> 00:07:17,000
You were just heartbroken last month,
and now there's already someone new?

132
00:07:17,083 --> 00:07:19,250
Mihan, I'm okay.

133
00:07:19,333 --> 00:07:22,958
You're the one who takes forever to heal.

134
00:07:24,333 --> 00:07:26,208
-Wow!
-[Mihan's mom laughs]

135
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:28,375
-Bye.
-[Mihan's mom] Okay.

136
00:07:32,333 --> 00:07:33,458
Charlie?

137
00:07:34,083 --> 00:07:35,625
Charlie, why are you here?

138
00:07:35,708 --> 00:07:37,125
Did she kick you out?

139
00:07:37,208 --> 00:07:39,708
-What happened? You had a fight?
-[Rafa] Charlie, wait!

140
00:07:40,208 --> 00:07:42,375
What are you doing to my friend?

141
00:07:42,458 --> 00:07:44,375
It's extremely hot,
and you're making her wait here!

142
00:07:44,458 --> 00:07:45,500
[Rafa, in English]
I never asked her to move out.

143
00:07:45,583 --> 00:07:47,250
She's just being overly dramatic.

144
00:07:47,333 --> 00:07:49,750
Wow, now you're calling her overdramatic?

145
00:07:49,833 --> 00:07:52,000
You have a lot to say about my friend.

146
00:07:52,083 --> 00:07:54,250
[in Filipino] You're second-guessing
our whole relationship.

147
00:07:54,333 --> 00:07:58,500
All I said was that maybe
we moved in too fast.

148
00:07:58,583 --> 00:08:00,375
[in English] I mean, we've only been
together for a couple of months.

149
00:08:00,458 --> 00:08:02,125
[in Filipino] We both made that decision!

150
00:08:02,208 --> 00:08:04,125
[Rafa, in English]
When I showed a bit of hesitation

151
00:08:04,208 --> 00:08:06,500
[in Filipino] you told me that
I didn't love you enough.

152
00:08:06,583 --> 00:08:08,250
That I'm not all-in.

153
00:08:08,333 --> 00:08:10,500
So you were just pressured?

154
00:08:10,583 --> 00:08:12,625
[Rafa] All I'm saying is that
when you want something,

155
00:08:12,708 --> 00:08:14,333
you want to get it right away.

156
00:08:14,416 --> 00:08:17,125
I never had time to process,
and get to know what I wanted.

157
00:08:17,208 --> 00:08:19,875
And that should be okay,
but of course, it's not okay with you.

158
00:08:19,958 --> 00:08:23,708
-Now what? [sniffles] We're done?
-[Rafa scoffs]

159
00:08:23,791 --> 00:08:24,791
Here you go again.

160
00:08:24,875 --> 00:08:26,458
You want an answer, and you want it now.

161
00:08:27,083 --> 00:08:28,500
Can't I have some time to think?

162
00:08:37,833 --> 00:08:38,791
[Kit] Mm.

163
00:08:44,333 --> 00:08:45,625
That's a lot of stuff.

164
00:08:45,708 --> 00:08:47,250
Are you trying to woo someone?

165
00:08:47,333 --> 00:08:49,250
[breathy chuckle] You're ridiculous.

166
00:08:49,333 --> 00:08:50,875
It's been so long.

167
00:08:50,958 --> 00:08:53,125
-You're still not over Hannah?
-Wait, why are you out here?

168
00:08:53,208 --> 00:08:54,333
Why haven't you gone in yet?

169
00:08:54,416 --> 00:08:57,000
I've been ringing the doorbell for a
while, but no one's coming out.

170
00:08:57,083 --> 00:08:59,041
And no one's replying to my messages
in the group chat.

171
00:08:59,625 --> 00:09:03,166
-And Charlie, she's not replying...
-That's weird. Wait, I'll send a message.

172
00:09:03,250 --> 00:09:04,458
-Mm.
-Mm!

173
00:09:04,541 --> 00:09:07,333
I heard you're dating the painter.

174
00:09:07,416 --> 00:09:09,041
No way, that's fake news.

175
00:09:09,125 --> 00:09:10,333
-Fake news?
-Yeah.

176
00:09:10,416 --> 00:09:13,041
-I have a reliable source!
-[Mihan sighs]

177
00:09:13,125 --> 00:09:14,500
Let's talk about something else.

178
00:09:15,208 --> 00:09:16,500
Your outfit...

179
00:09:16,583 --> 00:09:17,500
What's wrong with my outfit?

180
00:09:17,583 --> 00:09:19,625
That's what you were wearing
in your Stories last night.

181
00:09:19,708 --> 00:09:21,000
[chuckles]

182
00:09:21,083 --> 00:09:22,875
Really, Kit?

183
00:09:22,958 --> 00:09:24,000
Whatever you say!

184
00:09:24,083 --> 00:09:24,916
Kit, you're impossible!

185
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:26,791
-Let's just wake up Hannah.
[Doorbell rings]

186
00:09:26,875 --> 00:09:30,250
Wake up!

187
00:09:30,333 --> 00:09:32,625
Charlie's going to
introduce her girlfriend later.

188
00:09:33,208 --> 00:09:34,958
How about you?
When will you introduce yours?

189
00:09:36,708 --> 00:09:37,791
Once you're back to being straight.

190
00:09:39,083 --> 00:09:41,000
-[in English] Okay, nice. Nice answer!
-[Kit chuckles]

191
00:09:41,083 --> 00:09:43,000
-[in Filipino] What?
-Move aside, come on.

192
00:09:43,083 --> 00:09:45,375
-What now?
-It's hot out here. Let's go inside.

193
00:09:45,458 --> 00:09:46,750
You still have a key?

194
00:09:46,833 --> 00:09:48,833
Let's go.

195
00:09:49,708 --> 00:09:52,125
-[car approaches]
-[Kit] You still have a key.

196
00:09:52,625 --> 00:09:54,083
[car doors open, close]

197
00:09:57,708 --> 00:09:59,708
-[Mihan] Hey, Tiff.
-[Charlie] Hi, Tiff.

198
00:10:00,791 --> 00:10:02,625
Hannah, I'm begging you.

199
00:10:02,708 --> 00:10:04,166
Take a sick leave this week.

200
00:10:04,250 --> 00:10:08,333
My mom said you haven't been
feeling well for two weeks now.

201
00:10:10,333 --> 00:10:11,458
[in English] Please?

202
00:10:12,083 --> 00:10:14,083
[in Filipino] Come on.

203
00:10:15,708 --> 00:10:17,375
[in English] One day.

204
00:10:17,458 --> 00:10:18,583
One week.

205
00:10:21,208 --> 00:10:22,333
Two days.

206
00:10:23,333 --> 00:10:25,000
That's final.

207
00:10:25,083 --> 00:10:26,416
Fine.

208
00:10:28,708 --> 00:10:31,625
I think I can still fix this, right?

209
00:10:31,708 --> 00:10:35,458
[in Filipino] I mean,
once I give Rafa the space she needs,

210
00:10:35,541 --> 00:10:36,916
she'll miss me.

211
00:10:37,583 --> 00:10:39,875
And maybe she'll change her mind.

212
00:10:39,958 --> 00:10:41,875
-[Mihan, in English] We can't blame her.
-[Hannah] Mm-hmm.

213
00:10:41,958 --> 00:10:44,000
[in Filipino] This?

214
00:10:44,083 --> 00:10:46,291
This isn't easy to understand or accept.

215
00:10:46,375 --> 00:10:47,291
[Charlie] Really?

216
00:10:47,375 --> 00:10:50,000
She's a lesbian.
This should be a no-brainer for her.

217
00:10:50,083 --> 00:10:54,375
Well, she probably gets it
but doesn't like it.

218
00:10:54,458 --> 00:10:57,791
Unbelievable.
We're bound to run into our exes.

219
00:10:57,875 --> 00:10:59,125
The world of queer women is really small.

220
00:10:59,208 --> 00:11:01,875
We don't really have a choice.
We don't have many options.

221
00:11:01,958 --> 00:11:03,458
[Mihan] If she's uncomfortable
about the whole set-up

222
00:11:03,541 --> 00:11:07,708
don't pressure her to meet us,
or be friends with us.

223
00:11:07,791 --> 00:11:09,166
[Kit] Is that possible?

224
00:11:09,250 --> 00:11:11,375
You're not friends with
your girlfriend's best friends?

225
00:11:11,458 --> 00:11:14,125
[in English] Charlie, you know
she wasn't very nice to you.

226
00:11:14,208 --> 00:11:16,125
-[Charlie] Right?
-[in Filipino] I witnessed it.

227
00:11:16,208 --> 00:11:18,125
She said I didn't care about her feelings.

228
00:11:18,208 --> 00:11:20,791
And when I'm right, I rub it in her face.

229
00:11:20,875 --> 00:11:25,208
She said I'm extremely opinionated,
and I'm unwilling to adjust for anyone.

230
00:11:27,333 --> 00:11:29,333
I see. So, you all agree?

231
00:11:29,416 --> 00:11:30,875
[overlapping chatter]

232
00:11:30,958 --> 00:11:33,416
[in English] Charlie, you have
a very strong personality.

233
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:36,625
[in Filipino] Charlie, what kind
of support do you really need?

234
00:11:36,708 --> 00:11:38,541
[in English] Real talk or blind followers?

235
00:11:38,625 --> 00:11:39,625
Blind followers!

236
00:11:39,708 --> 00:11:42,250
[Mihan, in Filipino] Then you'll surely
get back together!

237
00:11:42,333 --> 00:11:45,125
She won't be able to
sleep without you by her side!

238
00:11:45,208 --> 00:11:47,625
It will be hard for her to replace you,
I mean, look at that face.

239
00:11:47,708 --> 00:11:51,791
-Our friend is so beautiful!
-[overlapping chatter]

240
00:11:52,583 --> 00:11:54,375
-[Hannah] Really!
-Pretty damn gorgeous!

241
00:11:54,458 --> 00:11:55,875
That's right.

242
00:11:55,958 --> 00:11:57,208
[in English] Thank you.

243
00:11:57,791 --> 00:11:59,666
-[Mihan] You're welcome.
-Let's eat.

244
00:12:00,500 --> 00:12:01,666
[Charlie, in Filipino] Enough about me.

245
00:12:01,750 --> 00:12:03,625
I've had too much airtime already!

246
00:12:03,708 --> 00:12:05,208
Can we talk about something else?

247
00:12:05,291 --> 00:12:10,291
First of all, when are we visiting
the animal shelter with Mihan?

248
00:12:10,375 --> 00:12:11,875
I want to meet all the dogs!

249
00:12:11,958 --> 00:12:13,208
[in English] Guys, hard pass.

250
00:12:13,291 --> 00:12:15,041
-[Kit] Huh?
-I hate dogs.

251
00:12:15,125 --> 00:12:17,166
-Don't say that out loud!
-You hate dogs?

252
00:12:17,250 --> 00:12:18,125
[in Filipino] What's wrong with you?

253
00:12:18,208 --> 00:12:20,375
I was chased by a dog
when I was in second grade!

254
00:12:20,458 --> 00:12:22,625
Charlie, the dog just wanted
to play with you.

255
00:12:22,708 --> 00:12:25,333
And Charlie, dogs will love you
unconditionally,

256
00:12:25,416 --> 00:12:28,041
no matter what your attitude is.

257
00:12:28,125 --> 00:12:29,833
Why, what's my attitude?

258
00:12:32,625 --> 00:12:35,583
Kit, answer her! Kit, answer her.

259
00:12:36,583 --> 00:12:38,500
Nothing, I have no problem
with your attitude.

260
00:12:38,583 --> 00:12:39,458
I actually like it.

261
00:12:39,541 --> 00:12:41,625
[exclaim softly] Sorry.

262
00:12:41,708 --> 00:12:43,708
[Hannah] Second important thing, guys.

263
00:12:46,458 --> 00:12:48,791
Say your goodbyes to Tiff.

264
00:12:48,875 --> 00:12:52,583
[in English]
She's moving out this week.

265
00:12:53,166 --> 00:12:55,625
I've loved having her around here,

266
00:12:55,708 --> 00:12:58,250
[in Filipino] but guys, her family
already requested that

267
00:12:58,333 --> 00:13:01,583
we move her to her final resting place.

268
00:13:01,666 --> 00:13:03,750
Of course, I want to honor their wishes.

269
00:13:03,833 --> 00:13:05,000
They've been very generous

270
00:13:05,083 --> 00:13:07,625
[in English] for letting her stay
with me for the last, almost...

271
00:13:08,375 --> 00:13:09,958
It's been two years, guys.

272
00:13:10,958 --> 00:13:12,375
It's about time.

273
00:13:12,458 --> 00:13:13,291
[soft music playing]

274
00:13:13,375 --> 00:13:15,208
[Charlie, in Filipino]
I can't believe it's been two years.

275
00:13:15,291 --> 00:13:17,083
That went by fast.

276
00:13:19,041 --> 00:13:20,458
[doorbell rings]

277
00:13:41,625 --> 00:13:42,625
[Charlie clears throat]

278
00:13:43,583 --> 00:13:44,416
[in English] Hi.

279
00:13:45,791 --> 00:13:46,833
Hi.

280
00:13:48,208 --> 00:13:49,833
How's Hannah?

281
00:13:50,708 --> 00:13:51,875
Um...

282
00:13:55,125 --> 00:13:58,208
Well, her girlfriend died, so...

283
00:13:58,833 --> 00:14:01,208
[in Filipino]
Uh, she's been asking me to leave

284
00:14:01,291 --> 00:14:03,916
but I can't bring myself
to leave her because...

285
00:14:05,916 --> 00:14:08,000
I understand.

286
00:14:08,083 --> 00:14:09,625
[knocking on door]

287
00:14:12,083 --> 00:14:14,250
-Do you want me to open the door?
-Mm-hmm.

288
00:14:15,458 --> 00:14:16,750
[Kit clears throat]

289
00:14:18,708 --> 00:14:19,708
Come in.

290
00:14:24,125 --> 00:14:25,708
Hey. How's it going?

291
00:14:25,791 --> 00:14:27,458
[Kit] Long time.

292
00:14:34,250 --> 00:14:35,458
[in English] So...

293
00:14:37,208 --> 00:14:38,416
you guys are together?

294
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:41,916
-We're not...
-No! No.

295
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:43,875
-Okay.
-Yeah.

296
00:14:43,958 --> 00:14:47,000
[in Filipino]
We just thought of visiting Hannah.

297
00:14:47,833 --> 00:14:49,791
-[in English] Separately!
-Okay.

298
00:14:49,875 --> 00:14:51,666
[in Filipino]
Well, I've been here for almost a week.

299
00:14:51,750 --> 00:14:53,000
I literally just got here.

300
00:14:53,083 --> 00:14:54,750
-Okay.
-Yeah.

301
00:14:54,833 --> 00:14:56,583
-I just got here.
-Sure, sure.

302
00:14:59,500 --> 00:15:01,625
But where is Hannah?

303
00:15:01,708 --> 00:15:03,166
[Kit] She's in her room upstairs.

304
00:15:04,333 --> 00:15:05,958
[in English] Oh. Okay...

305
00:15:07,083 --> 00:15:08,458
[Kit, in Filipino]
Do you want to go check on her?

306
00:15:09,708 --> 00:15:11,083
Yeah.

307
00:15:13,250 --> 00:15:15,458
-[Charlie, in English] Okay, go ahead.
-I'll try.

308
00:15:24,416 --> 00:15:25,916
[sighs]

309
00:15:37,708 --> 00:15:39,458
It's really messy in here.

310
00:15:46,333 --> 00:15:49,333
[somber music playing]

311
00:15:52,333 --> 00:15:55,583
[in Filipino] Guys, let's eat?

312
00:15:56,708 --> 00:15:59,916
Then go get cleaned up after, okay?

313
00:16:02,833 --> 00:16:04,208
Let's go.

314
00:16:08,458 --> 00:16:09,583
Let's eat?

315
00:16:11,875 --> 00:16:13,625
-[Hannah] Why isn't it here?
-[Kit] What's going on?

316
00:16:13,708 --> 00:16:15,250
[Hannah] Why is it all gone?

317
00:16:15,333 --> 00:16:16,625
Move aside!

318
00:16:16,708 --> 00:16:18,375
Move aside, please!

319
00:16:18,458 --> 00:16:20,375
[Kit] Is there anything you need?

320
00:16:23,208 --> 00:16:24,625
How can I help?

321
00:16:24,708 --> 00:16:26,708
What do you need?

322
00:16:26,791 --> 00:16:28,750
It's all gone.

323
00:16:28,833 --> 00:16:30,333
There's nothing left anymore.

324
00:16:31,208 --> 00:16:32,875
What are you looking for?

325
00:16:32,958 --> 00:16:35,000
[sobbing]

326
00:16:37,708 --> 00:16:42,208
[shakily]
Tiff had this habit of shoving things...

327
00:16:43,708 --> 00:16:45,208
into the sofa.

328
00:16:45,958 --> 00:16:48,333
Receipts.

329
00:16:50,333 --> 00:16:51,916
Candy wrappers.

330
00:16:52,500 --> 00:16:54,375
Chip bags.

331
00:16:54,458 --> 00:17:00,666
Everything, and it used to drive me crazy
whenever she did it, again and again.

332
00:17:02,333 --> 00:17:04,166
She knew, but she continued
doing it to tease me.

333
00:17:05,458 --> 00:17:07,083
And now it's all gone.

334
00:17:09,750 --> 00:17:11,125
Hey, what happened?

335
00:17:11,208 --> 00:17:14,375
I've finished loading the stuff
into the car.

336
00:17:14,458 --> 00:17:16,375
Kit, what happened?

337
00:17:16,458 --> 00:17:19,166
Nothing. I'm so sorry.

338
00:17:21,458 --> 00:17:22,875
-[in English] It's okay.
-Sorry.

339
00:17:22,958 --> 00:17:24,625
You're okay. Breathe.

340
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:29,250
[in Filipino] Drink some water first.

341
00:17:29,333 --> 00:17:31,375
[Charlie] I've spoken to someone
regarding Tiff's belongings.

342
00:17:31,458 --> 00:17:32,916
They'll take care of everything.

343
00:17:39,583 --> 00:17:40,791
[in English] Everything?

344
00:17:44,833 --> 00:17:47,083
Yes, everything.

345
00:17:50,583 --> 00:17:52,125
I'm really sorry, guys.

346
00:17:52,208 --> 00:17:54,500
[in Filipino] I didn't mean
to take over your Sunday.

347
00:17:54,583 --> 00:17:57,708
I know you guys have a lot
of other things to do.

348
00:17:57,791 --> 00:18:00,125
It's fine. We're okay with it.

349
00:18:00,208 --> 00:18:03,750
[in English] Hey. Any excuse
to get out of the house, right?

350
00:18:04,458 --> 00:18:07,583
[in Filipino] Next Sunday,
you might need help again.

351
00:18:09,208 --> 00:18:12,125
Sundays are always the hardest.

352
00:18:12,208 --> 00:18:16,125
You know, most of the week
I'm busy working.

353
00:18:16,708 --> 00:18:18,583
But on Sundays, guys...

354
00:18:19,291 --> 00:18:21,125
It was our day. Me and Tiff's.

355
00:18:25,208 --> 00:18:28,125
And now it's so quiet.

356
00:18:29,083 --> 00:18:30,500
It's killing me.

357
00:18:32,250 --> 00:18:33,333
[in English] Thank you.

358
00:18:34,958 --> 00:18:37,083
[in Filipino] Thank you for being here.

359
00:18:37,166 --> 00:18:38,500
[Kit] Um...

360
00:18:38,583 --> 00:18:41,208
Do you want us to be around next Sunday?

361
00:18:41,291 --> 00:18:43,666
Promise we'll be loud enough
to kill the silence.

362
00:18:45,333 --> 00:18:46,708
We'll be here with you all day.

363
00:18:47,333 --> 00:18:48,583
[in English] Please?

364
00:18:50,166 --> 00:18:52,000
-[sobbing]
-All right then.

365
00:18:52,083 --> 00:18:53,416
Please...

366
00:18:56,833 --> 00:18:58,750
-You'll be fine.
-[sniffles]

367
00:19:04,958 --> 00:19:07,666
[Mihan] Are you sad about moving, Tiff?

368
00:19:09,916 --> 00:19:10,916
[sighs]

369
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:13,416
[in English] You know,
grief comes in waves.

370
00:19:14,458 --> 00:19:17,250
[in Filipino] But I have more
good days now than bad ones.

371
00:19:19,083 --> 00:19:22,333
-[Mihan, in English] That's good to hear.
-Mm-hmm.

372
00:19:22,833 --> 00:19:25,791
Sometimes, I even feel joy,
which surprises me.

373
00:19:26,833 --> 00:19:27,708
[in Filipino] But...

374
00:19:28,625 --> 00:19:33,083
I know things will feel different
once I move her urn.

375
00:19:38,333 --> 00:19:39,875
[Mihan] Do you...

376
00:19:42,708 --> 00:19:44,208
want me to sleep here tonight?

377
00:19:45,708 --> 00:19:49,208
So, you won't be alone.

378
00:19:50,875 --> 00:19:54,458
Uh... Yeah, I guess that's okay.

379
00:19:56,708 --> 00:20:00,708
Oh, right, I just remembered
I have to take Mom somewhere tomorrow.

380
00:20:00,791 --> 00:20:03,041
She's leaving early. Um...

381
00:20:04,083 --> 00:20:05,583
-[in English] Maybe next time?
-Yeah.

382
00:20:05,666 --> 00:20:07,875
-Yeah, next time. Mm-hmm.
-Yeah? Yeah.

383
00:20:18,458 --> 00:20:19,541
Hello.

384
00:20:20,083 --> 00:20:21,916
-Hi.
-[man] Honey!

385
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:24,375
Phoebe forgot her lunchbox.

386
00:20:24,458 --> 00:20:25,791
[in English] I'll bring it to her.

387
00:20:26,375 --> 00:20:27,958
Honey, this is Teacher Kit.

388
00:20:28,041 --> 00:20:30,166
She's Phoebe's homeroom adviser.

389
00:20:30,250 --> 00:20:32,166
-[Lance] Hi, I'm Lance. I'm Phoebe's dad.
-Hello, sir.

390
00:20:32,250 --> 00:20:35,000
Sorry if it's always my wife
who goes to the school activities.

391
00:20:35,083 --> 00:20:37,000
It's fine. No worries.

392
00:20:37,083 --> 00:20:39,875
Go ahead. I'll hand Phoebe her lunchbox.

393
00:20:41,208 --> 00:20:42,375
[in English] Thank you, Teacher Kit.

394
00:20:42,458 --> 00:20:45,125
-Thank you. Let's go, Alexa.
-Okay.

395
00:20:54,458 --> 00:20:56,000
I miss you, Rafa.

396
00:21:05,083 --> 00:21:06,750
[in Filipino] What can I do...

397
00:21:08,083 --> 00:21:09,416
to make things right between us?

398
00:21:11,375 --> 00:21:13,000
Is there a way to change your mind?

399
00:21:16,958 --> 00:21:18,875
[in English] You know what I need.

400
00:21:18,958 --> 00:21:20,000
Tell me.

401
00:21:23,791 --> 00:21:25,416
[Rafa, in English] I can never have
the peace of mind that I need

402
00:21:25,500 --> 00:21:28,250
[in Filipino]
if you're still very close to your exes.

403
00:21:28,333 --> 00:21:32,000
[in English] If you have to make a choice
will you choose me?

404
00:21:32,708 --> 00:21:34,458
You want me to...

405
00:21:36,708 --> 00:21:38,541
totally cut them off?

406
00:21:40,208 --> 00:21:42,916
[Rafa] I would never make you
do something you don't want to.

407
00:21:45,458 --> 00:21:47,333
But I'm also setting my boundaries.

408
00:21:57,583 --> 00:21:59,833
I respect your boundaries.

409
00:22:02,083 --> 00:22:07,958
[in Filipino] And I understand
why you're asking for that.

410
00:22:09,875 --> 00:22:11,333
I'm sorry.

411
00:22:13,333 --> 00:22:15,583
I just can't imagine myself
disappearing from their lives.

412
00:22:17,583 --> 00:22:18,916
I'm sorry.

413
00:22:26,833 --> 00:22:31,625
-["Porque" by Maldita playing]
-♪ Staring blankly in my room ♪

414
00:22:31,708 --> 00:22:36,375
♪ Getting lost in my thoughts ♪

415
00:22:36,458 --> 00:22:41,000
♪ Couldn't stop myself from asking ♪

416
00:22:41,083 --> 00:22:45,750
♪ "Where the hell did I go wrong?" ♪

417
00:22:45,833 --> 00:22:47,750
-Hannah.
-[in English] Take it away!

418
00:22:47,833 --> 00:22:53,000
-♪ Why did I even fall for you? ♪
-[cheering]

419
00:22:53,083 --> 00:22:55,125
[in Filipino] Don't come closer, Mihan.

420
00:22:55,208 --> 00:22:57,375
-[in English] Stop!
-[Mihan laughs]

421
00:22:57,458 --> 00:23:01,625
♪ You disappeared out of the blue ♪

422
00:23:01,708 --> 00:23:03,208
[Mihan] You're having way
too much fun there!

423
00:23:03,291 --> 00:23:04,625
[Kit] What a voice!

424
00:23:05,208 --> 00:23:10,291
-♪ Why did it have to be you? ♪
-Whoo! Mihan's voice is so cool!

425
00:23:10,375 --> 00:23:14,833
-♪ Now my heart is breaking ♪
-It's like aircon blasting!

426
00:23:14,916 --> 00:23:17,125
-♪ All I ever wanted ♪
-Heartbreaker.

427
00:23:17,208 --> 00:23:19,458
♪ All I ever wanted ♪

428
00:23:19,541 --> 00:23:24,750
♪ Was for you to feel what I have felt ♪

429
00:23:24,833 --> 00:23:26,958
Go, Kit! Your turn!

430
00:23:27,791 --> 00:23:30,166
Come on, Kit! Don't be shy!

431
00:23:30,250 --> 00:23:33,958
There's no one else around, it's just us.

432
00:23:35,333 --> 00:23:38,291
♪ I pray with all my heart ♪

433
00:23:38,875 --> 00:23:45,041
-That's our Charito Lyn! Go!
-♪ That I could erase you from my mind ♪

434
00:23:45,125 --> 00:23:50,625
[all singing]
♪ Why did it have to be you? ♪

435
00:23:50,708 --> 00:23:56,125
♪ Now my heart is breaking ♪

436
00:23:56,208 --> 00:24:02,000
♪ All I ever wanted ♪

437
00:24:02,083 --> 00:24:09,083
♪ Was for you to feel what I have felt ♪

438
00:24:09,166 --> 00:24:13,125
♪ I pray for a miracle ♪

439
00:24:13,208 --> 00:24:16,208
♪ To turn back time ♪

440
00:24:16,291 --> 00:24:20,625
♪ To fix my mistakes ♪

441
00:24:20,708 --> 00:24:27,375
♪ I pray with all my heart ♪

442
00:24:27,458 --> 00:24:32,125
♪ That I could erase you from my mind ♪

443
00:24:32,208 --> 00:24:34,458
-[song ends]
-[all laugh]

444
00:24:36,500 --> 00:24:39,750
[Hannah] That was fun!
What's our next song?

445
00:24:40,333 --> 00:24:42,083
What's so funny?

446
00:24:42,166 --> 00:24:43,833
-What is it?
-Hey.

447
00:24:44,958 --> 00:24:45,875
Hey, watch your step.

448
00:24:45,958 --> 00:24:47,166
Come on! Why is this thing in the way?

449
00:24:47,250 --> 00:24:53,208
Go ahead, grab some shorts
from the closet.

450
00:24:54,208 --> 00:24:55,041
[Kit chuckles]

451
00:24:55,125 --> 00:24:57,333
[Charlie]
Marikit, your room looks really girly.

452
00:24:58,583 --> 00:25:00,500
Hey, I'm still in the closet.

453
00:25:00,583 --> 00:25:02,875
They're really religious.

454
00:25:02,958 --> 00:25:05,833
I won't come out
while they're still alive.

455
00:25:05,916 --> 00:25:07,208
[thuds, then vibrates]

456
00:25:07,291 --> 00:25:10,208
-What the hell?
-[Charlie laughs]

457
00:25:11,833 --> 00:25:14,375
[Kit] Give it to me! Don't touch it!

458
00:25:14,458 --> 00:25:19,250
Your parents would totally freak
if they saw this.

459
00:25:19,333 --> 00:25:21,708
-[in English] I have my needs, okay.
-Okay.

460
00:25:22,833 --> 00:25:25,125
Shirt. Shorts.

461
00:25:25,208 --> 00:25:26,083
[Charlie, in Filipino]
I was just looking for shorts

462
00:25:26,166 --> 00:25:27,625
but your drawer's got all sorts.

463
00:25:27,708 --> 00:25:29,583
[chuckles] Go change before...

464
00:25:29,666 --> 00:25:30,750
[exhales sharply]

465
00:25:32,541 --> 00:25:34,625
-Why? You've seen it all before.
-[Kit grunts]

466
00:25:34,708 --> 00:25:37,958
[Kit] I mean...

467
00:25:38,833 --> 00:25:40,500
Respect, you know?

468
00:25:48,083 --> 00:25:49,000
Are you done?

469
00:25:50,375 --> 00:25:51,208
[Kit chuckles]

470
00:26:12,458 --> 00:26:14,958
Honestly, it's her loss.

471
00:26:15,041 --> 00:26:16,791
You're gorgeous.

472
00:26:17,333 --> 00:26:19,250
You're smart.

473
00:26:19,333 --> 00:26:21,375
And you have very low standards.

474
00:26:21,458 --> 00:26:24,875
You won't have trouble
finding someone new.

475
00:26:24,958 --> 00:26:29,250
You're crazy. Rafa's not the one
I'm thinking of.

476
00:26:29,333 --> 00:26:30,416
Then what?

477
00:26:31,583 --> 00:26:33,875
I mean, it's not just Rafa.

478
00:26:34,750 --> 00:26:35,958
Well, who else?

479
00:26:37,875 --> 00:26:39,333
I was thinking

480
00:26:39,416 --> 00:26:43,250
maybe the reason I want a stable
romantic relationship is because

481
00:26:43,333 --> 00:26:46,625
I want someone to share life with.

482
00:26:47,166 --> 00:26:50,125
A partner I can rely on.

483
00:26:52,000 --> 00:26:53,125
You know?

484
00:26:53,208 --> 00:26:55,000
I'm always the one everyone relies on,

485
00:26:55,083 --> 00:26:57,000
the one taking care of everything.

486
00:26:57,083 --> 00:27:01,125
My parents. My siblings, their kids.

487
00:27:01,208 --> 00:27:03,416
[groans]

488
00:27:07,875 --> 00:27:11,208
Don't worry,
if it's about the electric bill

489
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:14,541
I'll take care of it.

490
00:27:15,833 --> 00:27:19,375
You're crazy,
I can find a way to handle that.

491
00:27:20,583 --> 00:27:21,916
In times like this,
you've still got so much pride?

492
00:27:22,750 --> 00:27:24,000
Charlie, I'm being serious.

493
00:27:24,083 --> 00:27:26,875
If you need help, just let me know.

494
00:27:28,500 --> 00:27:30,208
-Mm?
-Mm-hmm.

495
00:27:32,208 --> 00:27:33,625
Fine.

496
00:27:33,708 --> 00:27:36,041
If I ever need to borrow money,
you'll be the first person I ask.

497
00:27:36,125 --> 00:27:37,083
[Kit chuckles]

498
00:27:37,958 --> 00:27:39,166
That's a promise, okay?

499
00:27:43,083 --> 00:27:45,333
Go ahead, sleep now. Good night!

500
00:27:45,416 --> 00:27:51,416
Hey, don't go.
I don't wanna be alone here.

501
00:27:52,833 --> 00:27:55,166
Hold on, I haven't changed yet.

502
00:27:55,250 --> 00:27:56,583
That's fine!

503
00:27:57,375 --> 00:27:59,708
[Kit] You changed out of your clothes.

504
00:28:02,250 --> 00:28:03,125
[grunts]

505
00:28:08,416 --> 00:28:09,416
[clears throat]

506
00:28:10,541 --> 00:28:11,666
[sighs]

507
00:28:13,083 --> 00:28:15,041
Hey, Kit...

508
00:28:15,125 --> 00:28:16,125
[grunts]

509
00:28:16,958 --> 00:28:18,500
Don't even think about
getting into anything serious, okay?

510
00:28:19,458 --> 00:28:21,458
Your flings are enough.

511
00:28:22,250 --> 00:28:24,375
Love's nothing but heartache.

512
00:28:25,833 --> 00:28:28,833
[both laugh]

513
00:28:38,875 --> 00:28:41,125
Okay, my little gremlins...

514
00:28:41,208 --> 00:28:43,541
Get in the car!

515
00:28:44,250 --> 00:28:45,291
[in English] You know what I'm saying?

516
00:28:45,375 --> 00:28:47,000
[Hannah] I know what you're saying!

517
00:28:48,000 --> 00:28:50,375
[all laugh]

518
00:28:51,416 --> 00:28:52,666
Thank you.

519
00:28:54,125 --> 00:28:55,458
[in Filipino] I can do this!

520
00:28:57,041 --> 00:28:59,666
[laughing continues]

521
00:28:59,750 --> 00:29:00,958
Where are we going next?

522
00:29:01,041 --> 00:29:03,500
Why did we even go to that bar?
No one's cute anyway.

523
00:29:05,250 --> 00:29:06,625
Where are we going next?

524
00:29:07,125 --> 00:29:08,958
Want to hit the fast food drive-thru?

525
00:29:09,041 --> 00:29:10,666
I already know where we're headed next.

526
00:29:10,750 --> 00:29:13,833
Just rest, I've got you guys.

527
00:29:13,916 --> 00:29:17,041
[in English] Let's throw up together.
One, two, three!

528
00:29:17,125 --> 00:29:18,916
[playfully retches]

529
00:29:19,000 --> 00:29:21,125
[laughs]

530
00:29:21,208 --> 00:29:23,208
[warm music playing]

531
00:29:39,000 --> 00:29:40,791
[Kit, in Filipino] Why are we spending
our Sunday here?

532
00:29:40,875 --> 00:29:44,333
I hope no one sees me in this outfit.

533
00:29:44,416 --> 00:29:46,541
I don't want to ruin a possible fling.

534
00:29:46,625 --> 00:29:49,125
[Mihan] I don't understand
why Hannah canceled last minute.

535
00:29:49,208 --> 00:29:53,416
When I called her earlier
she said her house was messy.

536
00:29:53,500 --> 00:29:55,125
That's really weird.

537
00:29:55,208 --> 00:29:58,291
Looks like our food's gonna get here
before Hannah does.

538
00:29:58,375 --> 00:30:00,291
[in English] She's never late.

539
00:30:00,375 --> 00:30:01,875
[in Filipino] Is Hannah okay?

540
00:30:03,250 --> 00:30:04,666
She hasn't replied in the group chat

541
00:30:04,750 --> 00:30:06,291
after she said we should spend
our Sunday here.

542
00:30:06,875 --> 00:30:08,250
What if something happened?

543
00:30:08,333 --> 00:30:09,416
Should we go to her place?

544
00:30:09,500 --> 00:30:12,333
I have a feeling
she's keeping something from us.

545
00:30:13,291 --> 00:30:15,416
I can feel it.
Hannah's not usually like this.

546
00:30:19,250 --> 00:30:22,916
Wait, what if she's dating
that annoying girl from her office?

547
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:24,833
The one who's so into her?

548
00:30:24,916 --> 00:30:26,666
What's her name again?

549
00:30:26,750 --> 00:30:28,458
Sheena? Was that Sheena?

550
00:30:28,541 --> 00:30:29,666
[Mihan] No, Sheena's
the other annoying one!

551
00:30:29,750 --> 00:30:32,416
The closet homophobe
who's pretending to be an ally,

552
00:30:32,500 --> 00:30:34,166
giving all those backhanded compliments.

553
00:30:34,250 --> 00:30:36,833
She said I was so pretty
so why don't I have a boyfriend?

554
00:30:36,916 --> 00:30:38,083
I hope it's not her.

555
00:30:38,166 --> 00:30:40,458
-[in English] I hate that girl!
-[Mihan] Yuck!

556
00:30:40,541 --> 00:30:42,541
Hey, guys, sorry I'm late.

557
00:30:45,166 --> 00:30:46,250
[sighs]

558
00:30:46,333 --> 00:30:47,875
[in Filipino] Uh, we already ordered food.

559
00:30:47,958 --> 00:30:50,208
I'll get the menu,
just in case you want something.

560
00:30:50,291 --> 00:30:52,666
No, it's okay. I'm good.

561
00:30:52,750 --> 00:30:54,458
[Charlie] Why are you still standing?

562
00:30:54,541 --> 00:30:55,666
Are you okay?

563
00:30:55,750 --> 00:30:57,333
Also, why don't you want
to spend today at your place?

564
00:30:57,416 --> 00:30:58,916
-What's wrong?
-Um...

565
00:31:00,875 --> 00:31:02,125
Okay, I'll just say it.

566
00:31:02,208 --> 00:31:05,541
Because if I don't,
I won't be able to say it later.

567
00:31:06,625 --> 00:31:09,166
You're all my best friends, right?

568
00:31:09,250 --> 00:31:10,666
-So...
-[waiter, in English] Excuse me.

569
00:31:10,750 --> 00:31:14,083
You'll understand me. You have to.

570
00:31:18,625 --> 00:31:22,041
[in Filipino]
I think you should just eat first.

571
00:31:22,125 --> 00:31:24,166
-[in English] Thank you.
-[in Filipino] I want that...

572
00:31:24,791 --> 00:31:26,708
Hold up! Come on.

573
00:31:26,791 --> 00:31:29,041
Nobody eats until Hannah finishes
what she's gonna say.

574
00:31:29,125 --> 00:31:30,666
[Kit] I'm starving...

575
00:31:30,750 --> 00:31:33,541
You're hungry? Later, later.

576
00:31:33,625 --> 00:31:34,541
Go ahead, Hannah.

577
00:31:35,666 --> 00:31:37,791
[in English] Okay, fine.
I'll just say it. Um...

578
00:31:41,166 --> 00:31:42,333
Uh...

579
00:31:43,250 --> 00:31:44,458
I'm engaged.

580
00:31:46,875 --> 00:31:49,833
I'm engaged to...

581
00:31:50,416 --> 00:31:51,708
Matteo.

582
00:31:52,625 --> 00:31:54,291
[in Filipino] What? Who's that?

583
00:31:56,833 --> 00:31:59,041
Hold on. Is this a prank?

584
00:31:59,125 --> 00:32:02,416
[Charlie and Kit laugh]

585
00:32:02,500 --> 00:32:04,041
Why aren't you laughing? It's funny.

586
00:32:04,125 --> 00:32:07,208
I've known Matteo
for a long time through work

587
00:32:07,958 --> 00:32:12,041
[in English] but I only really got to
know him better these past few months.

588
00:32:12,125 --> 00:32:13,750
And guys, we instantly hit it off.

589
00:32:13,833 --> 00:32:16,791
It was a real connection,
and everything was great.

590
00:32:16,875 --> 00:32:17,791
So smooth.

591
00:32:17,875 --> 00:32:21,666
[in Filipino] Then he proposed,
and I said yes.

592
00:32:24,500 --> 00:32:26,375
Exactly when was a few months ago?

593
00:32:27,041 --> 00:32:30,208
-W-What's his last name?
-Why didn't you tell us sooner?

594
00:32:30,291 --> 00:32:32,958
How long have you two been together?

595
00:32:33,041 --> 00:32:34,666
[Mihan] Are you pregnant?

596
00:32:34,750 --> 00:32:35,791
Is that why
you're getting married so soon?

597
00:32:35,875 --> 00:32:38,791
You don't have to get married
just because you're pregnant.

598
00:32:38,875 --> 00:32:40,833
Wait, I really don't get it, Hannah.

599
00:32:40,916 --> 00:32:42,416
Why didn't you tell us?

600
00:32:42,500 --> 00:32:44,750
[in English]
I just wanted to make sure first.

601
00:32:45,500 --> 00:32:47,625
[in Filipino] I wanted to see
where it will go.

602
00:32:47,708 --> 00:32:49,250
I really wanted to tell you,

603
00:32:49,333 --> 00:32:53,000
[in English] something important
would come up, and...

604
00:32:53,083 --> 00:32:54,666
[in Filipino] so I didn't get the chance.

605
00:32:54,750 --> 00:32:57,958
[in English] Wow, that last part...

606
00:32:59,041 --> 00:33:00,625
kinda bullshit.

607
00:33:05,625 --> 00:33:08,416
We've been together for five months.

608
00:33:08,500 --> 00:33:10,666
Five months?
[in Filipino] And you're getting married?

609
00:33:10,750 --> 00:33:11,916
[in English] He's very sure of me.

610
00:33:12,000 --> 00:33:13,541
Are you sure about him?

611
00:33:13,625 --> 00:33:15,125
You barely even know him.

612
00:33:18,000 --> 00:33:19,916
[in Filipino] Is this going to be
a long engagement

613
00:33:20,000 --> 00:33:23,416
or are you getting married soon?

614
00:33:23,500 --> 00:33:26,375
[in English] I know him well enough and...

615
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:29,166
Yes, we'll get married very soon.

616
00:33:29,250 --> 00:33:31,541
[in Filipino]
Actually, the reason I'm late is that

617
00:33:31,625 --> 00:33:34,166
a potential buyer came to the house.

618
00:33:34,750 --> 00:33:38,500
Well, guys, after the wedding,
we're moving to a smaller place.

619
00:33:38,583 --> 00:33:42,875
So this is just an FYI, huh?

620
00:33:43,458 --> 00:33:45,166
[in English] I don't get it.
You love that house.

621
00:33:45,250 --> 00:33:48,041
Yeah, but guys, it was too big anyway.

622
00:33:48,875 --> 00:33:49,791
-Hannah, why?
-[Kit] Wait.

623
00:33:49,875 --> 00:33:51,666
[in Filipino] Hannah,
are you losing your mind?

624
00:33:51,750 --> 00:33:52,791
Is this a cry for help?

625
00:33:52,875 --> 00:33:55,791
[in English] Charlie,
this is what I've always wanted.

626
00:33:56,375 --> 00:34:00,041
[in Filipino]
Someone who is very sure of me.

627
00:34:00,125 --> 00:34:02,500
[in English]
Someone that wants to do life with me.

628
00:34:02,583 --> 00:34:06,416
I've never had a family
and I've always wanted one.

629
00:34:06,500 --> 00:34:09,208
And I don't mean family
in the heteronormative sense.

630
00:34:09,291 --> 00:34:10,541
I...

631
00:34:10,625 --> 00:34:13,208
I would've done all of these with a woman.

632
00:34:13,291 --> 00:34:14,916
[in Filipino]
It's just that no one ever gave me

633
00:34:15,000 --> 00:34:17,333
[in English]
the same level of assurance as he did.

634
00:34:22,375 --> 00:34:24,000
[in English]
We tell each other everything.

635
00:34:25,833 --> 00:34:28,250
[in Filipino] How were you able
to keep this from us for five months?

636
00:34:30,250 --> 00:34:31,833
I got scared.

637
00:34:32,416 --> 00:34:34,541
I got scared of how you'd react.

638
00:34:34,625 --> 00:34:36,208
What if you didn't like it, right?

639
00:34:36,291 --> 00:34:39,541
[in English] Then I'll start
second-guessing my own decisions

640
00:34:39,625 --> 00:34:41,791
and then everything
will just start falling apart.

641
00:34:41,875 --> 00:34:43,708
I mean, it's happening now.

642
00:34:43,791 --> 00:34:46,125
[chuckles] Wait, wait, wait.

643
00:34:46,208 --> 00:34:51,333
[in Filipino] Isn't it unfair to expect us
to support you right away

644
00:34:51,416 --> 00:34:53,041
after you just said all that?

645
00:34:53,875 --> 00:34:58,000
[in English] I know that's fair.
I'm really sorry.

646
00:34:58,750 --> 00:35:01,250
I'm... I'm sorry, guys.

647
00:35:01,333 --> 00:35:04,000
[in Filipino] I also can't stay long,
I need to leave because...

648
00:35:04,583 --> 00:35:07,791
yeah, sorry, I have a flight
to Dumaguete with Matteo.

649
00:35:07,875 --> 00:35:09,500
I'm meeting his family.

650
00:35:10,500 --> 00:35:13,750
But promise, please,
when I get back, let's talk, okay?

651
00:35:15,125 --> 00:35:16,333
[in English] Okay, guys? Please.

652
00:35:16,416 --> 00:35:18,833
I'm really sorry, I really need to go now.

653
00:35:28,625 --> 00:35:29,916
[in Filipino] I don't feel like
eating anymore.

654
00:35:33,291 --> 00:35:36,625
[bar music playing in the background]

655
00:35:40,916 --> 00:35:41,958
[sighs]

656
00:35:42,041 --> 00:35:44,708
This is driving me crazy.

657
00:35:45,291 --> 00:35:46,291
I'm going home.

658
00:35:46,375 --> 00:35:49,583
Being around you guys reminds me
of what happened earlier.

659
00:35:49,666 --> 00:35:50,666
Are you for real?

660
00:35:50,750 --> 00:35:51,916
I'm going home.

661
00:35:52,000 --> 00:35:55,291
Then I'll make a group chat
with just the three of us.

662
00:35:55,375 --> 00:35:57,708
I'll name it "Lesbians4Life."

663
00:35:59,125 --> 00:36:01,041
I'm leaving now, bye!

664
00:36:18,541 --> 00:36:20,000
Are you okay, Mihan?

665
00:36:23,166 --> 00:36:24,291
I'll just go to the bathroom.

666
00:36:36,083 --> 00:36:37,333
[door opens]

667
00:36:43,625 --> 00:36:44,583
Hi, Miss.

668
00:36:45,333 --> 00:36:46,666
Looks like you're alone.

669
00:36:46,750 --> 00:36:47,791
I'm sitting here, okay?

670
00:36:54,125 --> 00:36:55,916
I'm with someone.

671
00:36:57,500 --> 00:36:59,375
I already noticed you earlier.

672
00:37:00,875 --> 00:37:03,416
My friends and I are drinking
at the bar across the street.

673
00:37:04,000 --> 00:37:05,625
Actually, the vibes there are pretty okay.

674
00:37:06,500 --> 00:37:08,250
Come join us. You're alone anyway.

675
00:37:11,750 --> 00:37:13,416
You didn't hear me, did you?

676
00:37:13,500 --> 00:37:15,208
I said I'm with someone.

677
00:37:15,875 --> 00:37:17,083
Your boyfriend?

678
00:37:19,166 --> 00:37:22,375
Mmm... but I don't see any guy around.

679
00:37:28,791 --> 00:37:32,291
[sighs] Oh, damn... A girlfriend?

680
00:37:32,375 --> 00:37:33,500
You're with your girlfriend, huh?

681
00:37:35,750 --> 00:37:37,000
Whoa. I swear, the world's changed.

682
00:37:38,250 --> 00:37:40,333
A beautiful girl actually likes
another girl as hot as her.

683
00:37:45,000 --> 00:37:46,000
Where are you going?

684
00:37:46,583 --> 00:37:48,041
Go on, don't be shy.

685
00:37:48,125 --> 00:37:49,125
Give me a shot.

686
00:37:49,208 --> 00:37:50,916
[man] Maybe I've got something
your girlfriend doesn't.

687
00:37:51,000 --> 00:37:52,583
Or bring your girlfriend too.

688
00:37:52,666 --> 00:37:54,791
-Let's have a threesome.
-[Charlie] Get off me.

689
00:37:54,875 --> 00:37:56,291
Asshole!

690
00:37:56,375 --> 00:37:57,541
-Damn you, asshole!
-Fuck you.

691
00:37:57,625 --> 00:37:59,791
-[Charlie] Mihan, no!
-[Mihan] Get out!

692
00:37:59,875 --> 00:38:02,750
[bouncer] That's enough! Get out of here!

693
00:38:05,125 --> 00:38:06,500
Are you okay, Charlie?

694
00:38:06,583 --> 00:38:07,791
Are you hurt?

695
00:38:08,541 --> 00:38:09,875
Hey, are you really okay?

696
00:38:11,875 --> 00:38:13,250
Do you need anything?

697
00:38:15,500 --> 00:38:17,666
Mm-hmm. Yeah, I'm fine.

698
00:38:19,125 --> 00:38:22,666
Next time, don't just attack, Amihan.

699
00:38:22,750 --> 00:38:24,833
Let the security handle it.

700
00:38:24,916 --> 00:38:29,500
It's supposed to be a safe space,
and then some pervert just barges in.

701
00:38:32,541 --> 00:38:33,750
And despite all that,

702
00:38:33,833 --> 00:38:36,583
you still get the whole
"not all men" excuse.

703
00:38:36,666 --> 00:38:39,041
When you're with me,
remember no one can hurt you.

704
00:38:42,833 --> 00:38:44,541
Thanks for your perfect timing.

705
00:38:48,000 --> 00:38:51,583
Oh, my God! Today's just too much.

706
00:38:51,666 --> 00:38:53,041
Everything's so extra!

707
00:38:53,125 --> 00:38:54,416
First, there was some trashy guy.

708
00:38:54,500 --> 00:38:57,041
Then, my ex did a soft launch
of who she's seeing.

709
00:38:57,125 --> 00:38:59,750
And Hannah's getting married to...
[whispers] a guy!

710
00:39:00,333 --> 00:39:01,333
[sighs]

711
00:39:02,750 --> 00:39:04,541
Is Mercury in retrograde or what?

712
00:39:04,625 --> 00:39:09,416
-Seriously? Your ex is with someone new?
-Mm-hmm.

713
00:39:09,500 --> 00:39:12,125
Yeah, but the photo's all blurred out
'cause it's just a soft launch.

714
00:39:12,708 --> 00:39:14,000
Forget about your ex.

715
00:39:15,000 --> 00:39:16,291
You'll be fine.

716
00:39:17,000 --> 00:39:19,208
-You think so?
-Yes.

717
00:39:19,875 --> 00:39:22,208
[in English] You'll never be too much
for the right person.

718
00:39:23,500 --> 00:39:26,041
[in Filipino] Whoever ends up with you
will be so lucky.

719
00:39:31,625 --> 00:39:33,833
-If you say so.
-[chuckles]

720
00:39:34,833 --> 00:39:37,500
[Mihan] I mean it, okay?

721
00:39:39,333 --> 00:39:40,916
Believe me.

722
00:39:42,125 --> 00:39:43,291
I'll try.

723
00:39:43,375 --> 00:39:44,541
Promise?

724
00:39:44,625 --> 00:39:46,125
-Don't ever forget it.
-Mm-hmm.

725
00:39:50,083 --> 00:39:52,875
[both breathing heavily, moaning]

726
00:40:00,958 --> 00:40:02,333
What's the problem, Kit?

727
00:40:04,041 --> 00:40:05,166
[Kit sighs]

728
00:40:09,500 --> 00:40:10,791
-[sighs]
-[in English] What's wrong?

729
00:40:13,125 --> 00:40:14,791
[in Filipino] It's Hannah.

730
00:40:15,500 --> 00:40:17,250
I'm worried about her.

731
00:40:18,500 --> 00:40:20,500
She's been so supportive of us.

732
00:40:20,583 --> 00:40:22,541
I don't want to make her feel that...

733
00:40:22,625 --> 00:40:24,500
now that she's the one who needs us,

734
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:26,875
nobody understands her.

735
00:40:29,250 --> 00:40:32,708
[in English] Baby,
can you worry about her later?

736
00:40:33,250 --> 00:40:34,583
[in Filipino] I'm right here.

737
00:40:34,666 --> 00:40:37,041
We didn't come here to worry about that.

738
00:40:37,125 --> 00:40:39,166
Can you worry about her later?

739
00:40:40,250 --> 00:40:42,416
I'm sorry, it's just that...

740
00:40:42,500 --> 00:40:44,291
-I'll just leave if you can't focus on us.
-Wait.

741
00:40:45,375 --> 00:40:47,666
Please stay, Alexa. I'm sorry.

742
00:40:50,125 --> 00:40:51,458
Do you want me to go down first?

743
00:40:54,875 --> 00:40:56,333
I can't do it. I'm on my period.

744
00:40:59,416 --> 00:41:00,708
[Alexa sighs]

745
00:41:00,791 --> 00:41:04,250
They say when women spend a lot
of time together, their periods sync.

746
00:41:04,333 --> 00:41:06,875
Why won't ours line up?

747
00:41:07,875 --> 00:41:09,791
I don't know.
You hardly ever meet up with me.

748
00:41:13,875 --> 00:41:15,791
[phone ringing]

749
00:41:21,416 --> 00:41:23,416
[phone continues ringing]

750
00:41:26,375 --> 00:41:29,041
Who's that? One of your hookups?

751
00:41:31,500 --> 00:41:33,500
[in English]
I know you're sleeping around.

752
00:41:33,583 --> 00:41:34,500
I am.

753
00:41:35,500 --> 00:41:36,750
Okay. I don't care.

754
00:41:37,250 --> 00:41:39,000
[in Filipino] As long as you're only mine.

755
00:41:40,750 --> 00:41:42,875
[in English] Unfortunately... [chuckles]

756
00:41:43,666 --> 00:41:44,750
Why?

757
00:41:47,125 --> 00:41:50,333
Don't tell me
you're starting to want more?

758
00:41:51,125 --> 00:41:52,291
[in Filipino]
Kit, I thought you understood

759
00:41:52,375 --> 00:41:54,416
that this is all I could give you.

760
00:41:54,500 --> 00:41:57,250
And I'm sure,
if I were single and available,

761
00:41:57,333 --> 00:42:01,750
I'd be just like the others you message
but don't take seriously.

762
00:42:01,833 --> 00:42:02,708
[sighs]

763
00:42:04,291 --> 00:42:05,375
I don't know.

764
00:42:07,000 --> 00:42:09,541
I've never seen a version of you
that's available.

765
00:42:11,333 --> 00:42:12,875
[Mihan] "He can't believe it."

766
00:42:12,958 --> 00:42:16,791
"His tail wiggles like crazy!"

767
00:42:16,875 --> 00:42:19,416
"Even his little snipped ear
wiggles with happiness."

768
00:42:19,500 --> 00:42:22,416
"From that day on,
he's no longer a stray."

769
00:42:23,291 --> 00:42:25,458
"He's no longer a dog without a name."

770
00:42:26,250 --> 00:42:27,375
"His name is 'Snip.'"

771
00:42:28,083 --> 00:42:31,416
"And finally, he has a home."

772
00:42:32,000 --> 00:42:35,541
[audience applauding]

773
00:42:35,625 --> 00:42:38,000
Congratulations!

774
00:42:39,000 --> 00:42:41,041
Good afternoon, everyone!

775
00:42:41,125 --> 00:42:45,291
Again, thank you for coming
to the launch of our children's book,

776
00:42:45,375 --> 00:42:47,041
The Dog Without A Name.

777
00:42:47,125 --> 00:42:52,791
And now, we present the author,
Amihan Villanueva,

778
00:42:52,875 --> 00:42:55,541
our two-time
National Children's Book awardee.

779
00:42:55,625 --> 00:42:58,541
[in English] Again, we are Hiraya Press.
Thank you so much for coming!

780
00:43:00,416 --> 00:43:03,458
Part of the proceeds
from the book sales will go to PAWS,

781
00:43:03,541 --> 00:43:06,166
an animal shelter
that is very close to my heart.

782
00:43:06,250 --> 00:43:08,875
[in Filipino] I hope many of you
buy a copy.

783
00:43:08,958 --> 00:43:11,791
Consider it an early Christmas gift
for your godchildren.

784
00:43:11,875 --> 00:43:15,291
Or, I don't know,
maybe for your future kids?

785
00:43:15,375 --> 00:43:16,916
[Mihan and Charlie laugh]

786
00:43:17,000 --> 00:43:18,708
[in English] But thank you again!
[in Filipino] Thank you very much.

787
00:43:18,791 --> 00:43:20,166
-Congrats!
-[in English] Thank you!

788
00:43:24,125 --> 00:43:25,666
Thank you so much for coming.

789
00:43:25,750 --> 00:43:27,750
Charlie, why are you
so over the top today?

790
00:43:29,750 --> 00:43:33,416
[both] Congratulations!

791
00:43:34,000 --> 00:43:35,666
[in Filipino] Thank you, guys.
I really appreciate you coming.

792
00:43:35,750 --> 00:43:37,250
[Kit] Wait, where's Hannah?

793
00:43:37,333 --> 00:43:39,500
[huffs] Mm.

794
00:43:40,041 --> 00:43:42,041
[Mihan] She's turned into
a bouquet of flowers now.

795
00:43:42,125 --> 00:43:44,625
You know what, let it go.
She'll make it up to you.

796
00:43:44,708 --> 00:43:46,916
I'm sure Hannah will buy
a thousand copies anyway.

797
00:43:47,000 --> 00:43:49,041
-Will that even fix it?
-Hm?!

798
00:43:49,125 --> 00:43:50,208
You're so dramatic.

799
00:43:50,875 --> 00:43:52,333
[Mihan] So, dinner later?

800
00:43:52,416 --> 00:43:54,416
The book signing will be quick.
Just wait for me, please.

801
00:43:54,500 --> 00:43:56,791
-I'm all set!
-[exclaims]

802
00:43:57,375 --> 00:43:59,041
Go ahead and sign my books.

803
00:43:59,125 --> 00:44:00,666
[Mihan, in English]
As my super-supportive friend.

804
00:44:00,750 --> 00:44:03,416
[in Filipino] I wonder if our friend
Charlie is gonna buy one?

805
00:44:03,500 --> 00:44:05,666
Hey, I'll buy one!

806
00:44:05,750 --> 00:44:06,750
It's okay, she's saving up.

807
00:44:06,833 --> 00:44:08,041
-I'll buy one after!
-Okay, fine.

808
00:44:08,125 --> 00:44:09,416
But I'll get your autograph
another time, Mihan.

809
00:44:09,500 --> 00:44:10,541
-Because...
-Okay, sure.

810
00:44:10,625 --> 00:44:12,083
you guys go ahead and have dinner.

811
00:44:12,166 --> 00:44:14,916
I still need to find clients
for our open house this week.

812
00:44:15,000 --> 00:44:17,041
I'm going to get in trouble at work.

813
00:44:17,125 --> 00:44:19,541
Not happening.
Too much on my plate already.

814
00:44:19,625 --> 00:44:21,791
Okay, well, as our superwoman...

815
00:44:21,875 --> 00:44:23,916
I'm just gonna do the signing, okay?

816
00:44:24,000 --> 00:44:26,000
Go ahead.

817
00:44:29,125 --> 00:44:30,791
Come along later. It's my treat.

818
00:44:31,541 --> 00:44:32,416
Hey.

819
00:44:32,500 --> 00:44:34,666
I really can't.
I got work stuff to handle.

820
00:44:34,750 --> 00:44:36,166
[Kit] It'll be quick anyway.

821
00:44:36,250 --> 00:44:38,166
You know, I've got an idea.

822
00:44:38,250 --> 00:44:39,666
Why don't you just get
the autograph for me?

823
00:44:39,750 --> 00:44:42,125
Looks like you're itching
to get close to Mihan anyway.

824
00:44:42,625 --> 00:44:44,750
[in English] Are your guests
on the way, Charlie?

825
00:44:45,500 --> 00:44:46,583
Yes, ma'am.

826
00:44:46,666 --> 00:44:48,208
[in Filipino]
Maybe they're just stuck in traffic.

827
00:44:56,875 --> 00:44:58,000
[clears throat]

828
00:45:01,875 --> 00:45:04,125
[soft sentimental music playing]

829
00:45:04,208 --> 00:45:05,083
Hi.

830
00:45:06,625 --> 00:45:08,916
Hey, why are you here?

831
00:45:09,000 --> 00:45:10,250
I'm here as your potential client.

832
00:45:12,375 --> 00:45:16,750
You said you're in hot water at work
if you don't have clients, so...

833
00:45:17,500 --> 00:45:20,166
Right.

834
00:45:21,125 --> 00:45:22,083
But where is Kit?

835
00:45:23,000 --> 00:45:23,916
I don't know.

836
00:45:25,750 --> 00:45:28,375
Hang on, your boss is staring.

837
00:45:29,916 --> 00:45:35,291
Just pretend you can sell this to me
and I'll pretend I've got money to buy it.

838
00:45:35,375 --> 00:45:36,291
Game?

839
00:45:37,541 --> 00:45:39,333
-It all makes sense now!
-Hm?

840
00:45:39,416 --> 00:45:40,625
What is it?

841
00:45:40,708 --> 00:45:42,333
I've been having déjà vu...

842
00:45:42,916 --> 00:45:45,500
This is where we last ate
before you ghosted me.

843
00:45:46,875 --> 00:45:50,583
-You're funny. Come on, let's eat.
-Yeah, it's true!

844
00:45:52,875 --> 00:45:55,458
[in English] Oh, my God! I'm sorry.

845
00:45:57,291 --> 00:45:58,541
Oh my God, I'm so sorry.

846
00:45:58,625 --> 00:46:00,375
[in Filipino]
I'm so sorry, I didn't realize.

847
00:46:00,458 --> 00:46:03,375
It's just my favorite place, that's all.

848
00:46:04,125 --> 00:46:05,500
-I can tell.
-[Mihan] Sorry.

849
00:46:05,583 --> 00:46:07,500
That's exactly what you ordered back then.

850
00:46:08,250 --> 00:46:10,125
Seriously, I'm sorry.

851
00:46:11,750 --> 00:46:12,625
[sighs]

852
00:46:13,208 --> 00:46:14,291
It's fine.

853
00:46:15,291 --> 00:46:19,291
Honestly, it'd be weird
if it had worked out.

854
00:46:19,375 --> 00:46:21,333
We're both Hannah's exes, right?

855
00:46:21,416 --> 00:46:22,416
[Mihan chuckles]

856
00:46:24,000 --> 00:46:26,916
Charlie...

857
00:46:28,000 --> 00:46:29,666
[in English] Sorry for disappearing.

858
00:46:30,375 --> 00:46:33,583
I've wanted to reach out
and apologize so many times.

859
00:46:33,666 --> 00:46:36,291
[in Filipino] I don't know... [chuckles]

860
00:46:36,375 --> 00:46:40,333
I'm good at getting things going,
but I can't follow through.

861
00:46:40,416 --> 00:46:41,708
[Charlie] Hmm...

862
00:46:42,625 --> 00:46:43,875
Well, at least
you know that about yourself.

863
00:46:43,958 --> 00:46:44,791
[chuckles]

864
00:46:44,875 --> 00:46:47,750
I promise.

865
00:46:50,500 --> 00:46:52,416
I'm trying to change.

866
00:46:52,500 --> 00:46:53,875
[in English] Try harder!

867
00:46:53,958 --> 00:46:55,666
[in Filipino] Just kidding!

868
00:46:57,708 --> 00:46:58,958
[both giggle]

869
00:47:03,583 --> 00:47:05,250
Actually...

870
00:47:05,875 --> 00:47:06,791
I have a theory why I'm like this.

871
00:47:06,875 --> 00:47:09,041
This is just a theory, okay?
Not an excuse.

872
00:47:09,125 --> 00:47:10,500
Tell me.

873
00:47:10,583 --> 00:47:12,333
I hate it when things end...

874
00:47:13,333 --> 00:47:18,583
so I run away before it even gets there.

875
00:47:19,375 --> 00:47:21,333
-What?
-I don't know.

876
00:47:21,416 --> 00:47:26,416
All the relationships I know
ended badly. Okay?

877
00:47:26,500 --> 00:47:28,541
My parents split early.

878
00:47:28,625 --> 00:47:30,666
Whenever I get close
to one of my mom's partners,

879
00:47:30,750 --> 00:47:31,875
they'd just disappear.

880
00:47:32,625 --> 00:47:34,375
-Same with me and Hannah.
-Mm?

881
00:47:35,000 --> 00:47:36,541
But you're the one who ended it, right?

882
00:47:36,625 --> 00:47:37,791
Like I said...

883
00:47:39,000 --> 00:47:40,125
Mihan.

884
00:47:41,208 --> 00:47:43,041
Your theory is ridiculous.

885
00:47:43,125 --> 00:47:44,166
What if it works out?

886
00:47:44,250 --> 00:47:47,916
You'll never get anywhere
if you always keep one foot out the door.

887
00:47:48,000 --> 00:47:49,166
[clicks tongue, sighs]

888
00:47:49,250 --> 00:47:51,750
I'm not even sure
why I'm like this, but...

889
00:47:53,041 --> 00:47:54,750
I hope it goes away too.

890
00:47:56,458 --> 00:47:58,791
Do you want some cake?

891
00:47:58,875 --> 00:48:00,875
-Sure! Feed me!
-Okay, hold on...

892
00:48:02,041 --> 00:48:04,041
[soft romantic acoustic music playing]

893
00:48:10,000 --> 00:48:13,833
HANNAH, CAN WE

894
00:48:22,666 --> 00:48:25,916
[Hannah] Hi gays, I'm back in Manila!

895
00:48:26,000 --> 00:48:29,291
[in Filipino] Can we meet up, please?

896
00:48:29,375 --> 00:48:33,000
I know you might still be upset with me,
but I really need to hear from you.

897
00:48:33,875 --> 00:48:35,958
Come by the house this Sunday, please?

898
00:48:36,750 --> 00:48:38,250
[in English] I love you!

899
00:48:47,125 --> 00:48:49,458
[Charlie, in Filipino]
Where did you park your car?

900
00:48:49,541 --> 00:48:51,833
I don't drink and drive.

901
00:48:52,333 --> 00:48:53,750
[in Filipino] We'll book a ride.

902
00:48:54,250 --> 00:48:56,625
[in English]
Very, very responsible of you.

903
00:48:56,708 --> 00:48:58,750
Of course.

904
00:48:58,833 --> 00:49:00,125
-[Alexa] Hi!
-Okay, let's--

905
00:49:01,375 --> 00:49:02,375
[in Filipino] I thought you were sick?

906
00:49:06,208 --> 00:49:08,166
-I'm fine now.
-[Alexa] And who's this?

907
00:49:08,250 --> 00:49:10,041
This is...

908
00:49:11,125 --> 00:49:12,416
Hi, I'm Charlie!

909
00:49:12,500 --> 00:49:13,583
Charlie?

910
00:49:15,000 --> 00:49:17,375
Maybe you're not aware of Kit's modus.

911
00:49:17,458 --> 00:49:19,791
She's so beautiful, charming, and nice.

912
00:49:19,875 --> 00:49:22,625
You might also believe that
she really likes you, but she doesn't.

913
00:49:23,500 --> 00:49:25,125
[in English]
She'll forget about you tomorrow

914
00:49:25,208 --> 00:49:27,166
because this is a one-time thing.

915
00:49:27,875 --> 00:49:29,125
[in Filipino] She won't talk to you again,

916
00:49:29,208 --> 00:49:32,208
[in English]
so I guess enjoy it while it lasts.

917
00:49:34,750 --> 00:49:36,291
[in English] You know, woman...

918
00:49:36,375 --> 00:49:39,166
I don't know what your deal is
with my girlfriend.

919
00:49:39,250 --> 00:49:41,333
We've been together
for quite some time now.

920
00:49:41,416 --> 00:49:43,958
We're very, very happy.

921
00:49:44,041 --> 00:49:45,041
So, excuse us!

922
00:49:46,708 --> 00:49:47,833
[Charlie grunts]

923
00:49:47,916 --> 00:49:49,625
-[in Filipino] Attention seeker!
-[Kit grunts]

924
00:49:57,833 --> 00:50:01,375
[Charlie] I think I deserve to know
who I was yelling at.

925
00:50:01,458 --> 00:50:03,166
I totally lost it back there.
My English was running out.

926
00:50:03,250 --> 00:50:04,458
[both chuckle]

927
00:50:06,375 --> 00:50:08,000
[clicks tongue] All right.

928
00:50:09,625 --> 00:50:14,541
Just don't judge, okay?
Or... fine, whatever.

929
00:50:14,625 --> 00:50:16,958
I feel like I deserve to be judged anyway.

930
00:50:17,041 --> 00:50:19,125
That's Alexa.

931
00:50:19,916 --> 00:50:21,291
My girlfriend, I think?

932
00:50:21,875 --> 00:50:23,291
[chuckles]
Not even sure what to call us.

933
00:50:23,375 --> 00:50:25,291
Wait! You have a girlfriend?!

934
00:50:25,375 --> 00:50:26,791
Mm-hmm.

935
00:50:26,875 --> 00:50:28,625
-A girlfriend?!
-Yes.

936
00:50:30,000 --> 00:50:31,583
[gasps] Shit.

937
00:50:31,666 --> 00:50:34,666
What do I do? I'm really sorry!

938
00:50:34,750 --> 00:50:36,250
It's fine.

939
00:50:38,375 --> 00:50:39,875
She's married.

940
00:50:39,958 --> 00:50:44,083
Her kid is my student.
That's how we got to know each other.

941
00:50:45,458 --> 00:50:48,000
[in English] Holding my judgment.

942
00:50:48,083 --> 00:50:50,958
-[Kit chuckles]
-Tell me more.

943
00:50:51,041 --> 00:50:54,541
She said she's fine
with me sleeping around

944
00:50:54,625 --> 00:50:57,875
or seeing other people.

945
00:50:59,750 --> 00:51:01,708
[in Filipino] As long as I don't
catch feelings for anyone else.

946
00:51:03,625 --> 00:51:05,458
That they're all reserved for her.

947
00:51:06,583 --> 00:51:09,333
You know I'm fully supportive
of you, right?

948
00:51:10,208 --> 00:51:13,458
-Mm-hmm.
-But, damn, if the reason why

949
00:51:13,541 --> 00:51:16,041
you're shutting yourself off
from real connections

950
00:51:16,125 --> 00:51:19,791
is because some possessive
so-called girlfriend is controlling you.

951
00:51:21,833 --> 00:51:24,458
-[upbeat romantic nostalgic music playing]
-Kit! You're not a toy she can own.

952
00:51:25,500 --> 00:51:29,583
Have you seen her microbladed eyebrows?
So horrible!

953
00:51:29,666 --> 00:51:31,458
[muffled counting]

954
00:51:32,708 --> 00:51:35,125
[both laugh]

955
00:51:37,541 --> 00:51:39,083
What the hell?!

956
00:51:42,125 --> 00:51:43,625
Hand me a towel!

957
00:51:44,875 --> 00:51:46,000
I told you!

958
00:51:46,875 --> 00:51:49,541
I can't do this game!

959
00:51:49,625 --> 00:51:51,625
[in English] Sorry!

960
00:51:52,875 --> 00:51:55,291
[both exclaiming]

961
00:52:00,416 --> 00:52:03,333
[upbeat romantic nostalgic
music continues]

962
00:52:11,166 --> 00:52:14,708
[exclaiming]

963
00:52:14,791 --> 00:52:16,333
[Kit chuckles]

964
00:52:18,041 --> 00:52:20,166
[both laugh]

965
00:52:21,083 --> 00:52:22,958
You've been staring for a while now.

966
00:52:23,041 --> 00:52:24,541
Why? I can't help but stare at you.

967
00:52:24,625 --> 00:52:28,125
-[Charlie] Excuse me?
-No, nothing. Nothing!

968
00:52:28,750 --> 00:52:30,041
[Charlie] No fair.

969
00:52:30,125 --> 00:52:32,208
[groans] Seriously, thank you.

970
00:52:32,291 --> 00:52:35,166
Thank you for going along
with all my craziness.

971
00:52:35,250 --> 00:52:38,791
I really don't know
where I'd end up without you.

972
00:52:38,875 --> 00:52:41,666
I really appreciate it, Marikit!

973
00:52:41,750 --> 00:52:43,250
[in English] Thank you so much.

974
00:52:43,791 --> 00:52:47,666
[in Filipino] All this swag and you still
call me by my full-on girly name?

975
00:52:47,750 --> 00:52:50,250
-Okay, fine! I'll say it again.
-[Kit] Say it right this time.

976
00:52:51,375 --> 00:52:53,125
Kit. Kit!

977
00:52:53,208 --> 00:52:57,833
You're so handsome! You're so hot!

978
00:52:58,375 --> 00:53:00,416
You know, I'm not just saying this
because I'm drunk,

979
00:53:00,500 --> 00:53:05,416
but you're one of
the kindest people I know.

980
00:53:05,500 --> 00:53:06,333
For real?

981
00:53:06,416 --> 00:53:12,000
You don't deserve
to be kept a secret, or...

982
00:53:12,083 --> 00:53:16,666
or to settle for crumbs. Hell no!

983
00:53:16,750 --> 00:53:19,375
You deserve something real.

984
00:53:19,458 --> 00:53:23,041
You deserve someone
who wants to give you their all.

985
00:53:23,125 --> 00:53:25,000
That's what I want for you.

986
00:53:25,708 --> 00:53:27,166
-Mm.
-Mm-hmm.

987
00:53:28,791 --> 00:53:31,333
-Keep that in mind, okay?
-Okay.

988
00:53:34,208 --> 00:53:36,416
You're done touching my face? Do it again.

989
00:53:37,625 --> 00:53:39,416
-You're drunk!
-[laughs]

990
00:53:40,500 --> 00:53:43,291
Do it again, touch my face again.

991
00:53:43,375 --> 00:53:45,291
Hey, I'm really going to puke.

992
00:53:45,375 --> 00:53:46,916
Already?

993
00:53:47,000 --> 00:53:49,416
Damn, we've been drinking
since yesterday! [laughs]

994
00:53:49,500 --> 00:53:50,791
But this is what you wanted!

995
00:53:50,875 --> 00:53:53,791
You were the one who wanted to drink!

996
00:53:54,375 --> 00:53:58,791
[in English] So Phoebe's interactions
with her classmates has greatly improved.

997
00:53:58,875 --> 00:54:00,875
She's not shy or anxious anymore.

998
00:54:00,958 --> 00:54:02,666
And also she participates--

999
00:54:02,750 --> 00:54:04,958
[Alexa, in Filipino]
Why are you ignoring my messages?

1000
00:54:05,833 --> 00:54:08,208
So the girl that night
was really your girlfriend?

1001
00:54:09,958 --> 00:54:11,041
Don't do this here.

1002
00:54:11,125 --> 00:54:13,000
[Alexa, in English] Where? When?

1003
00:54:13,833 --> 00:54:15,458
I never see you
because you've been avoiding me.

1004
00:54:15,541 --> 00:54:20,041
Alexa, please. I'm at work,
and I'm following a schedule today.

1005
00:54:20,125 --> 00:54:21,583
[in English]
No, if we don't talk about this now,

1006
00:54:21,666 --> 00:54:22,541
then we're done.

1007
00:54:27,333 --> 00:54:28,166
Okay.

1008
00:54:30,583 --> 00:54:31,500
Okay?

1009
00:54:32,250 --> 00:54:33,916
[in Filipino] It's that easy for you?

1010
00:54:34,000 --> 00:54:35,375
Because you have someone new?

1011
00:54:39,583 --> 00:54:41,958
I've been thinking about this.

1012
00:54:42,875 --> 00:54:44,541
I'm not a homewrecker.

1013
00:54:45,208 --> 00:54:47,125
[in English] Yes, it was fun at first.

1014
00:54:47,791 --> 00:54:49,250
Yes, there was excitement and thrill.

1015
00:54:51,375 --> 00:54:53,000
But Alexa, this isn't me.

1016
00:54:55,625 --> 00:54:57,666
I'm not someone who chooses
to destroy someone else's life

1017
00:54:57,750 --> 00:54:59,458
just so I can be happy.

1018
00:55:05,500 --> 00:55:07,041
I love you.

1019
00:55:08,708 --> 00:55:10,625
[in English] Please tell me
what you need from me.

1020
00:55:13,791 --> 00:55:16,833
[in Filipino] Are you willing
to leave your husband for me?

1021
00:55:29,041 --> 00:55:31,166
[dogs barking]

1022
00:55:36,291 --> 00:55:38,291
[Mihan, in English]
Here, Lawson! Here, here!

1023
00:55:38,375 --> 00:55:39,750
-Oh!
-Oh, my God!

1024
00:55:39,833 --> 00:55:41,458
[in Filipino] What are you doing here?

1025
00:55:43,375 --> 00:55:46,666
I read your book

1026
00:55:46,750 --> 00:55:49,083
and I was encouraged
to come here and volunteer.

1027
00:55:50,250 --> 00:55:52,041
-But...
-[Mihan exclaims]

1028
00:55:52,750 --> 00:55:56,833
It's okay. Lawson is very nice.
Even nicer than you.

1029
00:55:56,916 --> 00:55:58,125
So mean!

1030
00:55:58,208 --> 00:56:00,750
Your timing is perfect!
Today is his walking day.

1031
00:56:00,833 --> 00:56:03,041
Join us! Let's go!

1032
00:56:03,625 --> 00:56:04,500
Game?

1033
00:56:04,583 --> 00:56:07,875
Don't be scared, he's really nice.

1034
00:56:10,000 --> 00:56:13,458
-Just try petting him. Try it once.
-[chuckles] Are you sure?

1035
00:56:14,541 --> 00:56:17,500
-[screams] Yay! That's enough!
-[laughs]

1036
00:56:18,083 --> 00:56:21,291
See, that wasn't so hard.
You can be a regular volunteer here.

1037
00:56:21,375 --> 00:56:22,625
Join me next time.

1038
00:56:25,000 --> 00:56:26,250
I'll think about it.

1039
00:56:28,541 --> 00:56:30,875
So, how are you?

1040
00:56:32,250 --> 00:56:34,416
We haven't heard from you in a while.

1041
00:56:35,083 --> 00:56:36,291
Are you feeling all sorts of ways?

1042
00:56:38,125 --> 00:56:39,708
I've always been this way.

1043
00:56:40,875 --> 00:56:43,750
[in English] About... Hannah's engagement?

1044
00:56:45,083 --> 00:56:47,666
I know. It's a loaded question.

1045
00:56:48,250 --> 00:56:50,750
[in Filipino] You don't have to answer
if you're not comfortable.

1046
00:56:53,041 --> 00:56:59,750
Uh, I'm still processing it,
so I can't really say how I am.

1047
00:57:00,750 --> 00:57:03,333
But I want her to be happy.

1048
00:57:05,750 --> 00:57:08,625
And I want to be happy for her.

1049
00:57:10,125 --> 00:57:11,250
But?

1050
00:57:20,583 --> 00:57:21,583
[chuckles sadly]

1051
00:57:25,416 --> 00:57:27,916
[Mihan] You have so many questions,
just give Lawson some treats.

1052
00:57:28,000 --> 00:57:31,000
-[laughs nervously] Wait!
-Come on, just one treat!

1053
00:57:32,750 --> 00:57:34,500
[psychiatrist, in English]
There's nothing wrong with having a crush.

1054
00:57:36,750 --> 00:57:38,375
[in Filipino] But I feel like
it's wrong because...

1055
00:57:39,208 --> 00:57:41,625
she's my ex, and we're best friends.

1056
00:57:42,750 --> 00:57:44,083
[psychiatrist] And?

1057
00:57:44,750 --> 00:57:48,791
I think the peace and balance
of our friendship

1058
00:57:48,875 --> 00:57:52,041
lie in the fact that we don't cross
that line with each other anymore.

1059
00:57:53,708 --> 00:57:54,666
[psychiatrist, in English]
You're all adults.

1060
00:57:54,750 --> 00:57:56,958
Maybe you should talk about it.

1061
00:58:01,291 --> 00:58:02,250
[in Filipino] It just frustrates me,

1062
00:58:02,333 --> 00:58:04,666
because the concept of friendship
is so beautiful, right?

1063
00:58:05,458 --> 00:58:07,625
It's so beautiful

1064
00:58:08,291 --> 00:58:10,791
but people act
like it's a consolation prize.

1065
00:58:11,750 --> 00:58:14,916
When someone gets friend-zoned,
they act like it's a loss.

1066
00:58:15,833 --> 00:58:18,666
But friendship is
the most beautiful thing in the world!

1067
00:58:18,750 --> 00:58:21,708
It's the most beautiful relationship
in the world.

1068
00:58:23,125 --> 00:58:25,375
With friendship, you're always sure.

1069
00:58:25,875 --> 00:58:28,500
Friendship is reliable.

1070
00:58:30,041 --> 00:58:32,541
[in English]
So, you're choosing friendship.

1071
00:58:33,791 --> 00:58:36,458
I think that's a good choice, yeah?

1072
00:58:38,750 --> 00:58:42,875
[in Filipino] I also don't want to jump
from one complicated set-up to another.

1073
00:58:43,583 --> 00:58:48,916
[in English] Kit, you're really self-aware
and that's a great thing.

1074
00:58:49,500 --> 00:58:51,000
Most people are not.

1075
00:58:51,583 --> 00:58:53,250
[Kit, in Filipino]
But you also know me well.

1076
00:58:53,833 --> 00:58:55,958
I always let my feelings win.

1077
00:58:56,833 --> 00:59:02,708
[in English] Well, it's a good thing
that feelings aren't facts.

1078
00:59:08,750 --> 00:59:09,833
Feelings aren't facts.

1079
00:59:10,333 --> 00:59:13,958
Feelings aren't facts.

1080
00:59:14,041 --> 00:59:15,875
-Hello!
-Feelings aren't facts.

1081
00:59:16,375 --> 00:59:17,291
Hey, Charlie!

1082
00:59:17,375 --> 00:59:20,500
-[Hannah] Hey, Charlie!
-Hello. Hi!

1083
00:59:21,291 --> 00:59:23,041
-Feelings aren't facts...
-[in Filipino] What is she saying?

1084
00:59:23,125 --> 00:59:24,958
I don't know.
She's been like that all day long.

1085
00:59:25,041 --> 00:59:26,208
-[chuckles]
-[in English] Feelings aren't facts.

1086
00:59:26,291 --> 00:59:28,291
[in Filipino] That's a lot. What's it for?

1087
00:59:28,375 --> 00:59:30,666
[in English] Shh! Quiet!
Feelings aren't facts.

1088
00:59:30,750 --> 00:59:33,166
-[in Filipino] I'm cooking tinola.
-Ah.

1089
00:59:33,250 --> 00:59:34,250
[Charlie exclaims]

1090
00:59:35,125 --> 00:59:36,708
Wow. Tinola!

1091
00:59:37,291 --> 00:59:39,750
Getting ready to be someone's wife?

1092
00:59:39,833 --> 00:59:41,041
[Hannah hums]

1093
00:59:41,125 --> 00:59:43,250
[Hannah, in English]
You're so funny, Charlie!

1094
00:59:43,333 --> 00:59:46,166
[in Filipino]
Can I explain our backstory first,

1095
00:59:46,250 --> 00:59:48,500
then you can all ask your questions later?

1096
00:59:48,583 --> 00:59:51,291
Mm-hmm. Sure, sure.

1097
00:59:52,166 --> 00:59:53,750
-Okay.
-Go!

1098
00:59:54,666 --> 00:59:57,500
Matteo's actually one of our clients.

1099
00:59:57,583 --> 00:59:59,333
I see him around

1100
00:59:59,416 --> 01:00:02,208
because we attend
the same meetings, same shoots.

1101
01:00:03,833 --> 01:00:08,666
He told me that
he had the biggest crush on me.

1102
01:00:08,750 --> 01:00:10,791
But he didn't pursue me or anything.

1103
01:00:10,875 --> 01:00:12,625
He had no idea if I was single.

1104
01:00:12,708 --> 01:00:15,458
[in English] And anyway,
he was a good client.

1105
01:00:15,541 --> 01:00:17,333
It was easy to get along with him.

1106
01:00:18,208 --> 01:00:20,125
[in Filipino]
Because he had a crush on you.

1107
01:00:20,208 --> 01:00:21,875
-[Charlie] Hm?
-[Hannah chuckles]

1108
01:00:22,458 --> 01:00:24,958
[in English] So last year
on a solo trip to Japan,

1109
01:00:25,458 --> 01:00:27,250
[in Filipino] my me-time trip.

1110
01:00:28,666 --> 01:00:30,541
[in English]
I ran into him in a restaurant.

1111
01:00:30,625 --> 01:00:34,291
[in Filipino] He asked
if he could join me, but I declined.

1112
01:00:34,375 --> 01:00:39,208
[in English] But after that, I would bump
into him in the most random places.

1113
01:00:39,708 --> 01:00:43,958
[in Filipino] I can understand seeing him
in Osaka, but Kobe, Nagoya...

1114
01:00:45,000 --> 01:00:49,166
I mean, these are
the most non-touristy places.

1115
01:00:49,250 --> 01:00:52,708
[scoffs] Some people call that stalking.

1116
01:00:53,208 --> 01:00:54,666
[Hannah chuckles]

1117
01:00:56,375 --> 01:00:59,166
[in Filipino] Eventually, I agreed
to have lunch with him

1118
01:00:59,250 --> 01:01:01,166
since I was nearing
the end of my trip anyway.

1119
01:01:01,250 --> 01:01:05,916
[in English] But lunch turned into dinner,
dinner turned into midnight snacks.

1120
01:01:06,000 --> 01:01:08,583
[in Filipino]
I hardly noticed the time passing

1121
01:01:08,666 --> 01:01:10,291
because I just felt so happy.

1122
01:01:10,375 --> 01:01:11,916
You know when you're just so comfortable,

1123
01:01:12,000 --> 01:01:15,041
you end up telling someone
your whole life story in a day?

1124
01:01:15,125 --> 01:01:16,958
That's how it was.

1125
01:01:17,041 --> 01:01:20,666
So, you've been talking since then?

1126
01:01:20,750 --> 01:01:22,333
[Hannah] Oh, no. Not yet,
because...

1127
01:01:23,125 --> 01:01:25,125
when I got back to Manila,
I crashed out.

1128
01:01:25,208 --> 01:01:27,416
We didn't talk for a while.

1129
01:01:28,125 --> 01:01:31,291
Imagine, right when I entered this house

1130
01:01:31,375 --> 01:01:33,750
it was Tiff's ashes that welcomed me home.

1131
01:01:33,833 --> 01:01:35,875
Of course, I felt guilty.

1132
01:01:36,791 --> 01:01:43,250
It felt wrong to feel happy
because Tiff just died.

1133
01:01:44,458 --> 01:01:46,208
[in English] That's not fair.

1134
01:01:46,291 --> 01:01:51,000
But at the same time,
I felt like I was letting a good thing go.

1135
01:01:52,916 --> 01:01:56,375
[in Filipino] So I talked to Tiff,
and I asked for her permission.

1136
01:01:57,208 --> 01:01:59,500
I don't have any proof but...

1137
01:02:00,500 --> 01:02:04,291
she gave me her permission to love again.

1138
01:02:09,458 --> 01:02:10,666
Guys, I'm really sorry.

1139
01:02:12,458 --> 01:02:14,541
I'm sorry that I wasn't able
to tell you right away.

1140
01:02:14,625 --> 01:02:15,791
I don't know...

1141
01:02:16,375 --> 01:02:19,666
I know that it was Tiff's death
and my grief that brought us together.

1142
01:02:19,750 --> 01:02:25,500
I didn't know how to admit to you,
or to myself, that I'm happy again.

1143
01:02:26,583 --> 01:02:27,875
Are you crazy?

1144
01:02:29,375 --> 01:02:34,416
Being exes with you isn't the only
common denominator between us three.

1145
01:02:35,000 --> 01:02:36,583
We want you to be happy.

1146
01:02:37,500 --> 01:02:38,583
[Kit] Genuinely happy.

1147
01:02:40,500 --> 01:02:42,416
[in English] Thanks, guys.

1148
01:02:42,500 --> 01:02:46,166
And if you ever change your mind
about the wedding, just give us a sign!

1149
01:02:46,250 --> 01:02:47,416
We'll all run away with you.

1150
01:02:47,500 --> 01:02:48,541
-Come on, guys!
-[in English] No questions asked.

1151
01:02:48,625 --> 01:02:52,500
-Blink twice, blink three times...
-[Kit] Yes, yes.

1152
01:02:52,583 --> 01:02:54,916
-...or give us those beautiful eyes.
-True.

1153
01:02:55,000 --> 01:02:57,541
We'll take it as a sign
that you want to be a runaway bride.

1154
01:02:57,625 --> 01:02:59,250
Yes.

1155
01:02:59,333 --> 01:03:00,166
[in Filipino] Hey, we're laughing now

1156
01:03:00,250 --> 01:03:02,833
but we seriously
got your back if you want out.

1157
01:03:04,625 --> 01:03:05,791
[in English] I love you guys.

1158
01:03:05,875 --> 01:03:08,333
And sorry for marrying a man!

1159
01:03:08,416 --> 01:03:12,541
It's always the bisexuals
getting the side-eye over stuff like this.

1160
01:03:12,625 --> 01:03:15,916
But hey,
he's the most evolved of his kind.

1161
01:03:17,125 --> 01:03:18,875
-Really?
-We'll see.

1162
01:03:19,583 --> 01:03:20,500
[in English] Promise!

1163
01:03:22,458 --> 01:03:25,875
[in Filipino] I'll miss this.
I'll miss hanging out here.

1164
01:03:36,666 --> 01:03:38,500
-[Mihan] You go ahead and step inside.
-[Kit] No, you first!

1165
01:03:38,583 --> 01:03:40,291
[Kit] You were together for five years.
Why don't you step in first?

1166
01:03:40,375 --> 01:03:41,916
[Hannah] Have you been out here long?

1167
01:03:42,875 --> 01:03:45,625
What are you doing just standing there?

1168
01:03:45,708 --> 01:03:46,541
-You go.
-You first.

1169
01:03:47,500 --> 01:03:49,333
-Seriously, come inside.
-[Charlie] Okay, fine.

1170
01:03:49,416 --> 01:03:50,500
Charlie, come on.
This is like your second home.

1171
01:03:50,583 --> 01:03:52,666
Mihan, could you please close the door?

1172
01:03:52,750 --> 01:03:55,791
Thank you all for coming.
I really appreciate it.

1173
01:03:55,875 --> 01:03:57,291
-Of course.
-[in English] Thank you so much.

1174
01:03:58,250 --> 01:03:59,291
Hi, love.

1175
01:03:59,916 --> 01:04:02,291
Guys, this is Matteo. My fiancé.

1176
01:04:02,375 --> 01:04:03,708
-Hi.
-This is Charlie.

1177
01:04:03,791 --> 01:04:04,875
-Charlie.
-Kit.

1178
01:04:04,958 --> 01:04:06,166
-And Mihan.
-Kit.

1179
01:04:06,250 --> 01:04:07,083
Mihan.

1180
01:04:07,166 --> 01:04:09,583
Nice to meet you guys.
I've heard so much about you.

1181
01:04:10,500 --> 01:04:12,041
[in Filipino]
I'm sure you're starving by now.

1182
01:04:12,125 --> 01:04:14,916
Oh, yeah, we're really hungry.

1183
01:04:15,000 --> 01:04:16,541
Wasn't this supposed to be brunch?

1184
01:04:16,625 --> 01:04:17,916
How did it turn into dinner?

1185
01:04:18,500 --> 01:04:19,416
What?

1186
01:04:19,500 --> 01:04:21,458
[Matteo] I'm so sorry about that.
That's my fault.

1187
01:04:21,541 --> 01:04:23,458
I really wanted to cook for all of you,

1188
01:04:23,541 --> 01:04:26,833
but I had to bring my parents
to the airport at lunchtime.

1189
01:04:26,916 --> 01:04:28,333
So I hope you understand.

1190
01:04:28,875 --> 01:04:30,791
-All right, let's eat. Love, let's go.
-Okay.

1191
01:04:30,875 --> 01:04:31,708
[Hannah] Let's go, love.

1192
01:04:31,791 --> 01:04:32,791
[in Filipino]
I think he's a good guy. Family man.

1193
01:04:32,875 --> 01:04:33,791
[Hannah] Come on. Matteo cooked.
Come on, guys.

1194
01:04:33,875 --> 01:04:35,375
[Matteo, in English]
Yeah, I cooked good food.

1195
01:04:35,458 --> 01:04:37,041
[in Filipino] Oh, love, sit here.

1196
01:04:37,125 --> 01:04:38,291
[Hannah] All right, thank you, love.

1197
01:04:38,375 --> 01:04:40,916
[in English] Charlie, you can sit
over there on the other side.

1198
01:04:41,000 --> 01:04:45,291
So, we've got veggies, medium-well steak,
Java rice and coleslaw.

1199
01:04:45,375 --> 01:04:47,000
Come on, let's eat.

1200
01:04:50,166 --> 01:04:51,875
Yeah, let's eat.

1201
01:04:51,958 --> 01:04:55,250
[utensils clinking]

1202
01:04:57,500 --> 01:04:59,500
-You want steak?
-Here you go, love.

1203
01:04:59,583 --> 01:05:03,541
It's okay.
I'll serve myself later. Thank you.

1204
01:05:11,625 --> 01:05:14,708
[in Filipino] Matteo, you rushed us
through everything.

1205
01:05:14,791 --> 01:05:16,125
Proposing?

1206
01:05:16,208 --> 01:05:18,666
Couldn't you have at least
courted her best friends first?

1207
01:05:18,750 --> 01:05:22,416
[in English]
Honestly, I am sorry about that, Kit.

1208
01:05:22,500 --> 01:05:24,708
[in Filipino] Guys, I wasn't hiding
from you or anything, okay?

1209
01:05:24,791 --> 01:05:29,041
It's just that Hannah here
took a while to be ready...

1210
01:05:29,625 --> 01:05:33,458
Like she didn't immediately realize
she was in love with me.

1211
01:05:34,166 --> 01:05:35,333
[coughs]

1212
01:05:36,791 --> 01:05:37,791
-So--
-[Mihan] Sorry.

1213
01:05:37,875 --> 01:05:39,166
-[Matteo, in English] The rice is okay?
-[Hannah, in Filipino] You okay, Kit?

1214
01:05:39,250 --> 01:05:41,333
Yes! Looks good!

1215
01:05:42,125 --> 01:05:43,625
[Charlie, in English] So, why the rush?

1216
01:05:43,708 --> 01:05:44,875
[in Filipino]
You haven't been together a year,

1217
01:05:44,958 --> 01:05:45,833
so why get married so soon?

1218
01:05:46,750 --> 01:05:49,416
You just sat down, and you're already
going for the main course?

1219
01:05:49,500 --> 01:05:51,958
-[all laugh]
-[Mihan] Look who's talking.

1220
01:05:52,666 --> 01:05:54,458
-Just kidding.
-Mihan...

1221
01:05:54,541 --> 01:05:55,875
[Mihan] Hey, that was just a joke.

1222
01:05:58,000 --> 01:05:59,791
I was just kidding...

1223
01:05:59,875 --> 01:06:01,000
[Charlie] So...

1224
01:06:01,916 --> 01:06:04,041
You're really head over heels
for our friend, huh?

1225
01:06:04,125 --> 01:06:07,375
Can't imagine life
without marrying her. Is that it?

1226
01:06:08,125 --> 01:06:09,250
[in English] Of course.

1227
01:06:09,875 --> 01:06:11,125
[Charlie, in Filipino] How many
girlfriends have you had?

1228
01:06:11,208 --> 01:06:13,166
[Matteo] Three.
Hannah's my fourth girlfriend.

1229
01:06:13,250 --> 01:06:14,791
[Charlie] How many of them
did you propose to?

1230
01:06:14,875 --> 01:06:15,791
[Matteo] Only Hannah.

1231
01:06:15,875 --> 01:06:17,291
[Charlie] Any history of cheating?

1232
01:06:17,875 --> 01:06:20,500
Yes... on my first girlfriend,
but that was in high school.

1233
01:06:20,583 --> 01:06:22,041
[Hannah, softly] Charlie!

1234
01:06:22,125 --> 01:06:24,291
[Kit] Is that supposed to be an excuse?

1235
01:06:24,375 --> 01:06:26,250
Seriously, Charlie? Can you stop already?

1236
01:06:26,333 --> 01:06:28,250
Why? He's answering.

1237
01:06:28,958 --> 01:06:30,041
What, are you scared of my questions?

1238
01:06:30,666 --> 01:06:31,500
Yes, I am.

1239
01:06:31,583 --> 01:06:33,875
-[Matteo grunts]
-[laughs, in English] You okay, love?

1240
01:06:33,958 --> 01:06:36,500
-Yeah, I'm all right.
-[in Filipino] You should be scared.

1241
01:06:36,583 --> 01:06:39,041
There are a lot of people
who care about Hannah.

1242
01:06:40,583 --> 01:06:42,208
[Charlie, in English] Last question!

1243
01:06:42,291 --> 01:06:43,875
Okay...

1244
01:06:44,875 --> 01:06:46,916
[in Filipino] Are you aware
that the Philippines and the Vatican

1245
01:06:47,000 --> 01:06:48,375
are the only places in the world
without divorce?

1246
01:06:48,958 --> 01:06:50,916
[in English] Um, no.

1247
01:06:51,000 --> 01:06:53,041
[Charlie, in Filipino]
Oh, so you didn't know!

1248
01:06:55,500 --> 01:06:56,458
[Matteo, in English] Noted.

1249
01:06:56,541 --> 01:06:57,416
[Charlie whispers, in Filipino]
The Philippines and the Vatican

1250
01:06:57,500 --> 01:06:59,208
are the only places
in the world without divorce.

1251
01:06:59,291 --> 01:07:01,541
[Kit whispers] Charlie, just eat.

1252
01:07:01,625 --> 01:07:04,250
-[Hannah, in English] You sure?
-[Matteo] Yeah, I'm fine.

1253
01:07:04,333 --> 01:07:05,541
[Hannah] Okay.

1254
01:07:06,583 --> 01:07:07,833
[chuckles]

1255
01:07:07,916 --> 01:07:10,416
[in Filipino] I told you,
you don't need to do all that.

1256
01:07:11,125 --> 01:07:15,541
Just relax. I've got this.

1257
01:07:16,875 --> 01:07:20,166
So this is what the deluxe service
feels like?

1258
01:07:20,250 --> 01:07:22,375
-And it won't run out, ma'am.
-[chuckles]

1259
01:07:22,875 --> 01:07:26,416
Tomorrow, I'll drop you off
and pick you up at the office.

1260
01:07:28,375 --> 01:07:31,416
So I won't have to deal
with traffic either?

1261
01:07:31,500 --> 01:07:35,541
Of course.
I've got it all handled, ma'am.

1262
01:07:35,625 --> 01:07:39,583
[in English] I love it! Thank you, sir.

1263
01:07:39,666 --> 01:07:41,250
[both chuckle]

1264
01:07:42,208 --> 01:07:44,416
So, Hannah...

1265
01:07:46,166 --> 01:07:47,291
[in Filipino] Still stressed?

1266
01:07:49,583 --> 01:07:51,458
That went well, right?

1267
01:07:52,125 --> 01:07:55,125
[in English] Um... I guess.

1268
01:07:55,208 --> 01:07:58,041
They're fun. I like your friends.

1269
01:07:58,125 --> 01:08:02,041
And I can see that they really love you.

1270
01:08:02,125 --> 01:08:03,833
I just hope that they like me.

1271
01:08:04,458 --> 01:08:06,250
Because I love you.

1272
01:08:07,500 --> 01:08:11,833
Aw. I love you, too. Thank you.

1273
01:08:13,750 --> 01:08:16,625
[in Filipino]
So who are you seeing this time?

1274
01:08:16,708 --> 01:08:19,583
-[chuckles]
-I haven't met him yet.

1275
01:08:20,375 --> 01:08:24,958
You two haven't met yet
because he still has to prove himself.

1276
01:08:25,666 --> 01:08:27,666
[in English]
Mihan, I'm just dating around.

1277
01:08:27,750 --> 01:08:29,500
[in Filipino] Don't worry about me.

1278
01:08:31,041 --> 01:08:33,416
Mom, how could I not worry about you?

1279
01:08:34,000 --> 01:08:35,500
I know you. You don't guard your heart.

1280
01:08:36,500 --> 01:08:39,291
[Mihan's mom, in English]
And you guard your heart way too much.

1281
01:08:40,750 --> 01:08:44,500
[in Filipino] So, has Hannah come home
from Dumaguete?

1282
01:08:46,750 --> 01:08:48,458
Has she explained herself?

1283
01:08:52,500 --> 01:08:53,666
[Mihan sighs]

1284
01:08:56,333 --> 01:08:57,333
I don't know, Mom.

1285
01:09:04,500 --> 01:09:07,333
I don't know why I'm like this.

1286
01:09:08,750 --> 01:09:12,208
I never did anything
to get her back before.

1287
01:09:12,791 --> 01:09:15,041
There's really no one else to blame.

1288
01:09:19,750 --> 01:09:21,458
[in English]
I just thought I had more time.

1289
01:09:21,541 --> 01:09:23,000
More time for what?

1290
01:09:25,625 --> 01:09:29,583
More time to withhold the love
she's always deserved?

1291
01:09:30,666 --> 01:09:34,458
More time to make her wait for a decision
that you should've made a long time ago?

1292
01:09:38,625 --> 01:09:39,916
[in Filipino] There's no point anymore.

1293
01:09:40,000 --> 01:09:41,458
[in English] Her mind's made up.

1294
01:09:43,500 --> 01:09:44,875
It's too late.

1295
01:09:46,750 --> 01:09:50,458
[Mihan's mom] If you had more time,
what would you do?

1296
01:09:53,875 --> 01:09:55,000
You know what, Mihan?

1297
01:09:55,583 --> 01:09:58,416
[in English] The only way for anyone
to be completely happy

1298
01:09:58,500 --> 01:10:02,333
is to open themselves up to everything.

1299
01:10:02,416 --> 01:10:05,916
To joy, to pain, to love.

1300
01:10:08,125 --> 01:10:09,750
[in Filipino]
Life isn't meant to be lived in fear.

1301
01:10:11,000 --> 01:10:14,416
[in English] It's such a waste,
don't you think?

1302
01:10:17,125 --> 01:10:19,208
[gentle music playing]

1303
01:10:33,916 --> 01:10:35,791
-[Hannah] It's been a while, Auntie Rina.
-[Mihan] What's going on here?

1304
01:10:35,875 --> 01:10:37,166
-[Hannah] Good morning!
-[Rina] Oh, wow!

1305
01:10:37,250 --> 01:10:39,166
-[Hannah] Oh, come on.
-We're just happy to see each other.

1306
01:10:39,250 --> 01:10:41,291
-[Rina] Just two gorgeous women bonding.
-[Hannah] True!

1307
01:10:41,375 --> 01:10:44,416
Wow, you two
are really flattering each other!

1308
01:10:44,500 --> 01:10:46,416
-Good morning.
-Good morning, Mom.

1309
01:10:46,500 --> 01:10:48,291
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

1310
01:10:49,500 --> 01:10:51,916
Mom, have you told her
you can't attend the wedding?

1311
01:10:52,000 --> 01:10:53,083
[Rina] Of course!

1312
01:10:53,166 --> 01:10:56,541
That's why Hannah's my favorite.
She's so understanding.

1313
01:10:56,625 --> 01:10:59,291
Hannah, darling,
even if I can't make it to your wedding

1314
01:10:59,375 --> 01:11:01,166
I'll make it up to you.

1315
01:11:01,250 --> 01:11:03,666
Do you want me to come on your honeymoon?

1316
01:11:03,750 --> 01:11:05,666
Sure, Auntie!
-[Mihan] Mom! Stop it.

1317
01:11:05,750 --> 01:11:07,416
-Oh, what? Then come join us too!
-[both laugh]

1318
01:11:07,500 --> 01:11:08,750
Let her be!

1319
01:11:08,833 --> 01:11:09,958
[in English] I have to go now.
I have a breakfast meeting.

1320
01:11:10,041 --> 01:11:11,291
-[in Filipino] Okay, Auntie.
-Good luck.

1321
01:11:12,416 --> 01:11:13,791
-[Mihan] Bye, Ma.
-[Rina] Bye, Mihan.

1322
01:11:13,875 --> 01:11:15,583
-Take care.
-Bye, darling.

1323
01:11:22,250 --> 01:11:23,708
[Mihan] Good luck for what?

1324
01:11:24,375 --> 01:11:27,375
-[in English] Good morning.
-Good morning.

1325
01:11:27,875 --> 01:11:29,083
Why are you here?

1326
01:11:29,625 --> 01:11:32,666
[in Filipino]
I cooked your favorite breakfast!

1327
01:11:32,750 --> 01:11:35,916
Onions and garlic
with a little corned beef.

1328
01:11:36,000 --> 01:11:37,625
-Mm-hmm.
-This feels like a bribe.

1329
01:11:38,500 --> 01:11:40,000
What do you need, huh?

1330
01:11:43,083 --> 01:11:46,625
I noticed you were
quiet last Sunday brunch.

1331
01:11:47,875 --> 01:11:49,541
How are you with Matteo?

1332
01:11:50,375 --> 01:11:51,791
He's all yours!

1333
01:11:51,875 --> 01:11:53,875
Mihan!

1334
01:11:55,625 --> 01:11:57,291
I'm okay. He's... okay.

1335
01:11:59,125 --> 01:12:00,666
You two seemed happy, so...

1336
01:12:01,458 --> 01:12:02,875
As long as you're happy

1337
01:12:04,166 --> 01:12:05,125
I'm okay.

1338
01:12:05,750 --> 01:12:08,250
You know what would make me even happier?

1339
01:12:13,125 --> 01:12:15,166
I knew this was a bribe.

1340
01:12:16,250 --> 01:12:17,250
What do you need?

1341
01:12:19,875 --> 01:12:22,125
Can you be my maid of honor?

1342
01:12:23,500 --> 01:12:25,791
-Don't you have other friends?
-Why?

1343
01:12:25,875 --> 01:12:28,958
You're my best friend. You know me best.

1344
01:12:29,625 --> 01:12:30,791
[in English] It makes sense.

1345
01:12:30,875 --> 01:12:33,291
[in Filipino]
But does Matteo know our history?

1346
01:12:33,375 --> 01:12:36,916
Yes! I tell him everything. Everything.

1347
01:12:37,000 --> 01:12:38,416
Ask him to be your maid of honor, then.

1348
01:12:38,500 --> 01:12:40,708
You're too much!

1349
01:12:46,791 --> 01:12:49,541
Mihan, I just don't show it but...

1350
01:12:50,250 --> 01:12:52,333
[in English] You know
I still have my fears and doubts

1351
01:12:52,416 --> 01:12:53,791
about what I'm doing.

1352
01:12:57,416 --> 01:13:00,291
[in Filipino] I don't know
what the ending will be.

1353
01:13:00,375 --> 01:13:03,833
But I know I'll be a lot calmer
with you beside me.

1354
01:13:07,041 --> 01:13:08,500
[in English] Please?

1355
01:13:11,958 --> 01:13:13,416
[in Filipino] Are you sure?

1356
01:13:13,500 --> 01:13:14,875
[in English] Please?

1357
01:13:17,541 --> 01:13:18,625
[sighs]

1358
01:13:21,208 --> 01:13:22,125
[sighs deeply]

1359
01:13:22,208 --> 01:13:23,750
[knocking on door]

1360
01:13:25,375 --> 01:13:27,041
[in English] Surprise!

1361
01:13:27,125 --> 01:13:30,000
Volunteer of the year.

1362
01:13:31,500 --> 01:13:32,791
[gasps]

1363
01:13:32,875 --> 01:13:33,833
Oh, sorry!

1364
01:13:33,916 --> 01:13:36,166
I didn't mean to barge in.
[in Filipino] Are you guys okay?

1365
01:13:36,250 --> 01:13:37,583
[in English] Yes, we're fine.
-It's okay.

1366
01:13:37,666 --> 01:13:38,875
-[Charlie] Sure?
-Yeah.

1367
01:13:39,791 --> 01:13:42,041
[Hannah] Nice to see you, Charlie.

1368
01:13:42,125 --> 01:13:43,208
[Mihan] Hi, Charlie.

1369
01:13:43,958 --> 01:13:45,916
Okay, yes!

1370
01:13:48,000 --> 01:13:50,208
[in Filipino] So, what's up?

1371
01:13:51,041 --> 01:13:53,291
Uh, I'll go with you
to the animal shelter.

1372
01:13:53,375 --> 01:13:55,000
I miss the dogs already.

1373
01:13:55,541 --> 01:13:58,375
-[Mihan exclaims]
-[laughs] Are you serious, Charlie?

1374
01:13:58,875 --> 01:14:01,541
Since when did you become a dog lover?

1375
01:14:01,625 --> 01:14:03,666
-You know, I was surprised too.
-Why?

1376
01:14:03,750 --> 01:14:07,541
She said she wants
to conquer her fear of dogs.

1377
01:14:08,375 --> 01:14:09,416
-I'm just encouraging her.
-Okay,

1378
01:14:09,500 --> 01:14:10,916
since she's already
wearing a "dog lover" shirt.

1379
01:14:11,000 --> 01:14:12,666
I think she's really serious this time.

1380
01:14:12,750 --> 01:14:16,125
Exactly, so I'll leave you two
so you can head out, okay?

1381
01:14:16,208 --> 01:14:17,416
[in English] Bye-bye.

1382
01:14:18,791 --> 01:14:20,125
Bye, guys.

1383
01:14:22,166 --> 01:14:23,375
[door closes]

1384
01:14:23,458 --> 01:14:25,083
-[in English] Let's go?
-Uh...

1385
01:14:25,166 --> 01:14:26,583
[in English] So...

1386
01:14:27,750 --> 01:14:29,250
Change of plans.

1387
01:14:29,875 --> 01:14:32,875
[in Filipino] We won't be playing
with the dogs today.

1388
01:14:36,375 --> 01:14:37,833
[in English] Momo was really old.

1389
01:14:38,750 --> 01:14:39,791
[sighs]

1390
01:14:40,500 --> 01:14:41,833
[in Filipino] He was already fifteen.

1391
01:14:42,500 --> 01:14:44,333
He was a grandpa dog at the shelter.

1392
01:14:45,708 --> 01:14:48,000
But he was one of my favorites.

1393
01:14:48,875 --> 01:14:50,208
He was like my shadow...

1394
01:14:51,708 --> 01:14:54,750
following me everywhere.

1395
01:14:58,916 --> 01:15:02,000
He'd had owners before...

1396
01:15:04,208 --> 01:15:06,666
but they abandoned him when he got sick.

1397
01:15:07,583 --> 01:15:10,541
He was used to people.

1398
01:15:12,708 --> 01:15:14,000
So kind,

1399
01:15:15,583 --> 01:15:17,000
so affectionate.

1400
01:15:19,166 --> 01:15:20,125
[sighs]

1401
01:15:21,208 --> 01:15:25,250
I actually regret not adopting him sooner.

1402
01:15:29,916 --> 01:15:30,750
[sighs]

1403
01:15:31,250 --> 01:15:33,458
[Charlie] Why didn't you adopt him?

1404
01:15:38,875 --> 01:15:40,458
[in English] Commitment issues.

1405
01:15:45,208 --> 01:15:46,750
Even with a dog?

1406
01:15:48,500 --> 01:15:50,041
[in English] Sorry, I can't catch a break.

1407
01:15:51,958 --> 01:15:53,583
It's loss after loss.

1408
01:15:55,083 --> 01:15:56,541
[in Filipino] Can I even handle this?

1409
01:15:59,458 --> 01:16:03,000
[in English]
Are we still talking about the dog?

1410
01:16:05,458 --> 01:16:06,291
[car doors closing]

1411
01:16:14,416 --> 01:16:16,458
I think she'll be genuinely happy.

1412
01:16:18,208 --> 01:16:19,166
Huh?

1413
01:16:21,875 --> 01:16:23,000
[in Filipino] I mean, Hannah...

1414
01:16:24,625 --> 01:16:27,125
I think she'll be happy with Matteo.

1415
01:16:29,208 --> 01:16:31,625
If that's what you're worried about?

1416
01:16:36,875 --> 01:16:38,708
[in English]
Is that what you're worried about?

1417
01:16:40,666 --> 01:16:41,916
[huffs]

1418
01:16:43,166 --> 01:16:46,750
I'm scared I'll lose her for good
once she marries him.

1419
01:16:49,125 --> 01:16:51,875
And if I lose her for good...

1420
01:16:53,250 --> 01:16:55,166
I'm scared I'll never be happy again.

1421
01:17:04,000 --> 01:17:05,250
You won't lose her.

1422
01:17:06,291 --> 01:17:07,833
We won't lose her.

1423
01:17:09,750 --> 01:17:10,833
And you will be happy.

1424
01:17:14,000 --> 01:17:15,333
I can't imagine it.

1425
01:17:21,833 --> 01:17:24,875
[upbeat romantic music playing]

1426
01:17:32,666 --> 01:17:33,666
[door closes]

1427
01:17:50,416 --> 01:17:53,000
[both chuckle]

1428
01:18:16,541 --> 01:18:18,750
[music abruptly stops]

1429
01:18:26,750 --> 01:18:28,875
[Mihan sighs, clears throat]

1430
01:18:32,625 --> 01:18:34,375
-[in Filipino] Excuse me! Let me see!
-[Charlie gasps]

1431
01:18:35,375 --> 01:18:39,041
-Here comes Marikit!
-She looks so lit!

1432
01:18:39,125 --> 01:18:42,791
-"So lit," what the heck? Stop it!
-[both giggle]

1433
01:18:42,875 --> 01:18:44,750
Are you comfortable
in what you're wearing?

1434
01:18:44,833 --> 01:18:46,541
I can't even walk properly.

1435
01:18:46,625 --> 01:18:48,916
I think I need to add a slit.

1436
01:18:49,000 --> 01:18:49,958
[both chuckle]

1437
01:18:50,041 --> 01:18:51,541
Like how?

1438
01:18:51,625 --> 01:18:53,791
-[Charlie] A slit, really?
-This high slit.

1439
01:18:53,875 --> 01:18:55,958
Guys, how does it look?

1440
01:18:57,041 --> 01:18:58,250
It's nice, right?

1441
01:19:00,083 --> 01:19:02,750
[Charlie exclaims happily]
You're so beautiful!

1442
01:19:02,833 --> 01:19:05,000
[Kit] You are the most beautiful bride
I've ever seen.

1443
01:19:06,875 --> 01:19:08,541
[Hannah] What do you think?

1444
01:19:08,625 --> 01:19:10,666
You're quiet, you don't like it on me?

1445
01:19:13,250 --> 01:19:15,333
What are you talking about?

1446
01:19:15,416 --> 01:19:16,875
Are you blind?

1447
01:19:17,916 --> 01:19:19,875
[Hannah chuckles]

1448
01:19:27,875 --> 01:19:29,625
-[Charlie] It's beautiful, Hannah.
-You think?

1449
01:19:29,708 --> 01:19:32,500
You all look so good, too.

1450
01:19:32,583 --> 01:19:35,166
Come here, let's check ourselves
in the mirror.

1451
01:19:36,500 --> 01:19:38,875
[Hannah exclaims softly]

1452
01:19:38,958 --> 01:19:42,333
["100 miles" by thesunmanager playing]

1453
01:19:58,000 --> 01:19:59,625
[Mihan] You look so good, baby.

1454
01:20:01,375 --> 01:20:05,333
The groom might get confused
and end up marrying you.

1455
01:20:05,416 --> 01:20:06,791
No!

1456
01:20:06,875 --> 01:20:09,916
Will I ever actually
become a bride, though?

1457
01:20:10,000 --> 01:20:11,041
[Mihan sighs]

1458
01:20:11,125 --> 01:20:14,291
[smacks lips]
It's not even legal in the Philippines.

1459
01:20:16,375 --> 01:20:17,875
Well, what if it was legal...

1460
01:20:21,500 --> 01:20:22,500
[Mihan sighs deeply]

1461
01:20:25,458 --> 01:20:28,666
[exhales, in English] 11:11, make a wish.

1462
01:20:30,125 --> 01:20:32,625
[in Filipino]
My wish won't come true anyway.

1463
01:20:38,125 --> 01:20:42,000
♪ The taste that you left behind ♪

1464
01:20:43,916 --> 01:20:47,416
♪ It feels like a hundred miles ♪

1465
01:20:48,500 --> 01:20:52,291
♪ Between you and me ♪

1466
01:20:53,791 --> 01:20:55,083
♪ I don't know ♪

1467
01:20:55,166 --> 01:20:58,291
-[in English] I love you.
-♪ If you remember me ♪

1468
01:20:58,958 --> 01:20:59,958
I love you.

1469
01:21:01,916 --> 01:21:05,750
♪ The taste that you left behind ♪

1470
01:21:08,125 --> 01:21:11,333
♪ It feels like a hundred miles ♪

1471
01:21:12,250 --> 01:21:16,125
♪ Between you and me ♪

1472
01:21:17,666 --> 01:21:20,708
♪ I don't know if you remember me ♪

1473
01:21:21,416 --> 01:21:23,041
-[song ends]
-[distant car engine running]

1474
01:21:28,333 --> 01:21:29,541
Good morning!

1475
01:21:29,625 --> 01:21:31,791
Are you losing your mind
over this wedding?

1476
01:21:33,125 --> 01:21:35,125
[Mihan coughs]

1477
01:21:36,375 --> 01:21:40,000
[Mihan retches]

1478
01:21:43,750 --> 01:21:44,750
[Mihan sighs]

1479
01:21:45,375 --> 01:21:46,583
-I'm really not feeling well.
-[in Filipino] Are you okay?

1480
01:21:46,666 --> 01:21:48,666
Maybe you should go without me.

1481
01:21:51,541 --> 01:21:52,916
[in English] Shut up.

1482
01:21:56,958 --> 01:21:58,625
[Kit, in Filipino] Hey, are you okay?

1483
01:22:01,750 --> 01:22:03,541
Hey, sorry I didn't join you last night.

1484
01:22:03,625 --> 01:22:05,083
I fell asleep early.

1485
01:22:05,166 --> 01:22:06,541
It's fine.

1486
01:22:06,625 --> 01:22:09,041
-So who did you end up inviting?
-[Mihan sighs]

1487
01:22:09,125 --> 01:22:10,541
I just stayed home alone.

1488
01:22:12,500 --> 01:22:13,625
Oh, so you drank last night.

1489
01:22:14,416 --> 01:22:16,000
That's why you woke up late?

1490
01:22:16,625 --> 01:22:17,458
Yes, I had some wine.

1491
01:22:19,208 --> 01:22:22,000
Why? Are you upset about something?

1492
01:22:28,041 --> 01:22:29,333
[Charlie laughs dryly]

1493
01:22:30,416 --> 01:22:31,791
[in English] Amazing!

1494
01:22:31,875 --> 01:22:33,875
[in Filipino] Come on, Kit, let's go!

1495
01:22:34,291 --> 01:22:35,625
Shall we?

1496
01:22:39,541 --> 01:22:40,458
[in English] Sure?

1497
01:22:41,333 --> 01:22:43,750
["Sssikreto" by Flying Ipis playing]

1498
01:22:45,500 --> 01:22:46,750
♪ Secret! ♪

1499
01:22:50,125 --> 01:22:51,750
♪ Shake your hips ♪

1500
01:22:54,500 --> 01:22:57,041
♪ One more time! ♪

1501
01:22:59,333 --> 01:23:02,208
-♪ I tell myself I must be insane ♪
-[in Filipino] Have we arrived?

1502
01:23:02,291 --> 01:23:03,375
Hey.

1503
01:23:04,041 --> 01:23:06,958
-[laughs]
-♪ Playing along this not crooked game ♪

1504
01:23:07,041 --> 01:23:08,083
[Charlie] What's so funny?

1505
01:23:08,166 --> 01:23:11,875
-What's with that face? Look at you!
-♪ Love is blind, pure, honest, and true ♪

1506
01:23:12,375 --> 01:23:15,666
♪ Enjoying the sand
Holding hands with you ♪

1507
01:23:15,750 --> 01:23:17,250
♪ He-he-hey! ♪

1508
01:23:17,333 --> 01:23:21,291
-♪ I'll just keep my love a secret ♪
-What's so funny?

1509
01:23:21,375 --> 01:23:24,125
-If you sleep, I'll sleep too!
-Everyone's sleeping?

1510
01:23:24,208 --> 01:23:25,958
♪ You just keep your "yes" a secret ♪

1511
01:23:26,041 --> 01:23:30,291
♪ I'll just keep my love a secret ♪

1512
01:23:30,375 --> 01:23:33,541
♪ You just keep your "yes" a secret ♪

1513
01:23:33,625 --> 01:23:35,041
♪ Come on! ♪

1514
01:23:35,125 --> 01:23:37,291
[song ends]

1515
01:23:37,375 --> 01:23:39,666
[in English] Hey everyone, welcome
to our pre-wedding dinner!

1516
01:23:39,750 --> 01:23:41,833
[in Filipino] We're so grateful
you could all make it.

1517
01:23:41,916 --> 01:23:43,416
If you look around,

1518
01:23:43,500 --> 01:23:47,750
the only ones invited are
our closest family and friends.

1519
01:23:47,833 --> 01:23:50,291
[in English] I'm sure most of you
will meet each other

1520
01:23:50,375 --> 01:23:52,000
for the first time tonight.

1521
01:23:52,083 --> 01:23:54,916
[Matteo] But before you all
head to the beach,

1522
01:23:55,000 --> 01:23:56,416
[in Filipino] I know the wedding vows
are for tomorrow,

1523
01:23:56,500 --> 01:23:58,291
[in English] but I will give you guys
a little snippet of it.

1524
01:23:58,375 --> 01:24:01,166
To the love of my life, Hannah,

1525
01:24:01,250 --> 01:24:06,833
I will do everything in my power
to always make you laugh and smile.

1526
01:24:06,916 --> 01:24:08,541
-[Hannah chuckles]
-I love you very much.

1527
01:24:08,625 --> 01:24:10,208
-Thanks, love. I love you.
-Love you.

1528
01:24:10,958 --> 01:24:13,916
-[crowd applauding]
-[in Filipino] Aw, that's so sweet!

1529
01:24:14,000 --> 01:24:15,291
[Kit] I know.

1530
01:24:16,666 --> 01:24:19,166
[chuckles] Looks like you're
getting eaten alive there!

1531
01:24:19,875 --> 01:24:21,458
Huh. What do you mean?

1532
01:24:21,541 --> 01:24:23,041
[Hannah, in English] Enjoy, guys!

1533
01:24:23,125 --> 01:24:24,208
Enjoy, please!

1534
01:24:24,291 --> 01:24:25,791
Help yourselves to the food and drinks!

1535
01:24:26,375 --> 01:24:27,250
[Kit, in Filipino] Be honest.

1536
01:24:27,333 --> 01:24:29,916
What's going on between you and Mihan?

1537
01:24:30,625 --> 01:24:35,666
-What?
-I'm feeling some kind of tension.

1538
01:24:35,750 --> 01:24:37,666
I just don't know where it's coming from.

1539
01:24:37,750 --> 01:24:39,416
That's nothing, come on!

1540
01:24:39,500 --> 01:24:41,125
[scoffs] Are you sure?

1541
01:24:41,875 --> 01:24:43,041
Earlier in the car,

1542
01:24:43,125 --> 01:24:45,375
it felt like you two
were about to kill each other.

1543
01:24:45,458 --> 01:24:46,750
What is it?

1544
01:24:47,291 --> 01:24:50,041
-I think you're upset.
-What the hell?

1545
01:24:50,125 --> 01:24:52,791
You're upset because Mihan invited me
for drinks last night and not you.

1546
01:24:52,875 --> 01:24:54,166
Are you upset, Charlie?

1547
01:24:54,250 --> 01:24:58,458
Forget it. It's just your imagination.

1548
01:24:58,541 --> 01:25:00,791
Stop with that little
conspiracy theory of yours!

1549
01:25:00,875 --> 01:25:02,875
[Kit] Whatever, I think you're upset.

1550
01:25:02,958 --> 01:25:04,166
Hey, who's upset with whom?

1551
01:25:04,250 --> 01:25:06,375
-That's why we're just standing here?
-She's just so upset.

1552
01:25:06,458 --> 01:25:08,125
-I don't know what she's talking about.
-Anyway, where's Mihan?

1553
01:25:08,750 --> 01:25:10,166
She went to the bathroom.

1554
01:25:10,250 --> 01:25:13,916
Okay, since there's some tension
and we're at the bar,

1555
01:25:14,000 --> 01:25:15,916
let's keep it chill, okay?

1556
01:25:16,000 --> 01:25:18,416
I don't want you getting drunk
and embarrassing me later.

1557
01:25:18,500 --> 01:25:20,291
You know what, just enjoy yourself.

1558
01:25:20,375 --> 01:25:22,166
We can handle ourselves, right?

1559
01:25:22,250 --> 01:25:24,166
-[Hannah] Hey, since when?
-We can totally handle ourselves.

1560
01:25:24,250 --> 01:25:25,125
Since when, huh?

1561
01:25:25,208 --> 01:25:26,833
[woman 1]
Luckily, Hannah's getting married.

1562
01:25:26,916 --> 01:25:28,916
I used to think she was
a lesbian growing up.

1563
01:25:29,000 --> 01:25:32,291
Good thing she changed,
and it was only a phase.

1564
01:25:32,375 --> 01:25:37,041
Even without her parents around,
she still found the right path.

1565
01:25:37,125 --> 01:25:41,166
Just give me the green light, Hannah,
and I'll take on your aunties for you.

1566
01:25:41,250 --> 01:25:43,458
-Don't mind them.
-Hey, easy, easy.

1567
01:25:43,541 --> 01:25:45,166
-Let's just have some shots.
-That's better.

1568
01:25:45,250 --> 01:25:47,375
-[bartender] Let's do shots.
-[Kit, in English] Thank you.

1569
01:25:48,291 --> 01:25:51,125
Later, let's have shots again
when Mihan gets back.

1570
01:25:57,000 --> 01:26:00,791
[exhales] Stay here, Charlie!

1571
01:26:00,875 --> 01:26:02,833
-Just ignore them.
-Take it easy.

1572
01:26:02,916 --> 01:26:05,333
Did you know one of my aunties there
is an MMA fighter?

1573
01:26:07,875 --> 01:26:09,875
[in English] Do you know
what's mind-blowing?

1574
01:26:12,375 --> 01:26:17,083
Hannah's face isn't even
the most beautiful thing about her.

1575
01:26:20,750 --> 01:26:21,750
It's her heart.

1576
01:26:21,833 --> 01:26:23,458
[gentle emotional music playing]

1577
01:26:23,541 --> 01:26:24,666
[exhales deeply]

1578
01:26:26,125 --> 01:26:28,166
[in Filipino] You know... [exhales]

1579
01:26:28,250 --> 01:26:31,750
I wasn't even supposed to march
at our college graduation.

1580
01:26:32,666 --> 01:26:33,916
[crying softly]

1581
01:26:34,666 --> 01:26:36,333
But Hannah found a way.

1582
01:26:38,166 --> 01:26:43,500
She figured out how to bug
the people around us to pitch in.

1583
01:26:44,500 --> 01:26:46,708
So I could pay my tuition balance
at Finance.

1584
01:26:50,250 --> 01:26:53,875
[sighs deeply] Oh, my God,
I'm crying again.

1585
01:26:54,291 --> 01:26:56,291
[sniffles, exhales]

1586
01:26:57,750 --> 01:27:02,583
[in English] So, Hannah, you deserve
all the love that you tirelessly shower

1587
01:27:02,666 --> 01:27:04,250
to everyone around you.

1588
01:27:05,375 --> 01:27:07,083
You deserve to be happy.

1589
01:27:08,000 --> 01:27:09,583
You deserve to be loved.

1590
01:27:10,333 --> 01:27:11,750
[in Filipino] You deserve everything.

1591
01:27:11,833 --> 01:27:14,791
And you deserve someone
who is so sure about you.

1592
01:27:14,875 --> 01:27:18,666
So sure that
he can't not marry you right now.

1593
01:27:19,625 --> 01:27:21,041
[in English] ASAP.

1594
01:27:21,125 --> 01:27:23,208
[in Filipino]
That's why we're all here, right?

1595
01:27:26,166 --> 01:27:27,375
Matteo...

1596
01:27:27,958 --> 01:27:30,541
[in English] You must've done
something right in this life

1597
01:27:30,625 --> 01:27:34,416
to deserve someone as beautiful
as my friend.

1598
01:27:37,125 --> 01:27:38,291
I love you, Hannah.

1599
01:27:40,750 --> 01:27:43,208
-Cheers, everyone!
-[all] Cheers.

1600
01:27:43,291 --> 01:27:46,083
[guests cheer, applaud]

1601
01:27:46,166 --> 01:27:47,250
[exhales deeply]

1602
01:27:49,500 --> 01:27:51,166
["Right Time" by Johnoy Danao
and Clara Benin playing]

1603
01:27:51,250 --> 01:27:53,833
-[in Filipino] Hello, aunties!
-Hi, Auntie.

1604
01:27:53,916 --> 01:27:55,625
-[in English] Thank you so much.
-Thanks so much for making the trip.

1605
01:27:56,333 --> 01:27:57,791
[in Filipino] Let's take a photo.

1606
01:27:57,875 --> 01:27:58,958
Cheers!

1607
01:27:59,041 --> 01:28:01,041
[both] Hello, Auntie Chad!

1608
01:28:03,833 --> 01:28:05,000
Dumaguete, represent!

1609
01:28:05,083 --> 01:28:06,208
Hey, gays!

1610
01:28:06,291 --> 01:28:11,541
♪ Pains of the past
Make for a guarded heart ♪

1611
01:28:11,916 --> 01:28:13,333
-[in English] Mihan, come closer.
-Mihan.

1612
01:28:15,500 --> 01:28:21,000
♪ But he saw her light
And walked right in ♪

1613
01:28:24,375 --> 01:28:28,500
♪ It felt familiar ♪

1614
01:28:29,375 --> 01:28:32,541
♪ Felt like home ♪

1615
01:28:33,916 --> 01:28:40,166
♪ With a broom in his hand
He swept her off her feet ♪

1616
01:28:43,916 --> 01:28:46,791
♪ Lonely days and nights ♪

1617
01:28:46,875 --> 01:28:49,875
♪ Have long been gone ♪

1618
01:28:52,666 --> 01:28:56,666
♪ What once was lost ♪

1619
01:28:56,750 --> 01:28:59,208
♪ Has now been found ♪

1620
01:29:02,000 --> 01:29:06,666
♪ Like the stars to the dreamers ♪

1621
01:29:06,750 --> 01:29:11,125
♪ Like the sea to the shore ♪

1622
01:29:11,750 --> 01:29:17,250
♪ With a hand to hold
The future has been told ♪

1623
01:29:20,125 --> 01:29:21,833
♪ And she said ♪

1624
01:29:21,916 --> 01:29:26,208
♪ It's the right time ♪

1625
01:29:26,291 --> 01:29:29,791
♪ To fall in love again ♪

1626
01:29:29,875 --> 01:29:30,875
[song ends]

1627
01:29:30,958 --> 01:29:33,958
[gentle waves lapping]

1628
01:30:04,916 --> 01:30:06,041
[in Filipino] Are you okay?

1629
01:30:12,500 --> 01:30:13,375
You sure?

1630
01:30:16,250 --> 01:30:17,791
Why do you keep on asking me that?

1631
01:30:18,875 --> 01:30:20,125
I said I'm fine.

1632
01:30:22,375 --> 01:30:25,375
Amihan, look at you!

1633
01:30:26,666 --> 01:30:29,541
I can literally see your inner chaos.

1634
01:30:29,625 --> 01:30:30,916
I'm not blind!

1635
01:30:31,000 --> 01:30:32,750
You've been cranky all day.

1636
01:30:35,500 --> 01:30:37,708
[in English] I don't know
what you want from me, Charlie.

1637
01:30:43,750 --> 01:30:45,125
-You know what?
-Hm?

1638
01:30:46,750 --> 01:30:48,916
It's Hannah's day, not yours.

1639
01:30:49,583 --> 01:30:50,833
[in Filipino] If you've got something
weighing on you

1640
01:30:50,916 --> 01:30:53,250
maybe hold off for now.

1641
01:30:54,416 --> 01:30:55,750
Can you at least fake a smile?

1642
01:30:56,333 --> 01:30:58,583
Try to be happy for her.

1643
01:30:59,000 --> 01:31:02,416
Pretend your whole world
isn't falling apart, just for today.

1644
01:31:05,125 --> 01:31:06,041
[sighs]

1645
01:31:11,208 --> 01:31:13,125
[footsteps approaching]

1646
01:31:13,208 --> 01:31:18,041
[laughs] The guy Hannah's marrying?

1647
01:31:18,125 --> 01:31:20,000
He's totally wasted!

1648
01:31:20,083 --> 01:31:21,458
What a weakling!

1649
01:31:22,000 --> 01:31:23,833
Hey, keep it down.

1650
01:31:24,500 --> 01:31:27,208
He might make Hannah the designated
driver once they're married.

1651
01:31:27,291 --> 01:31:28,791
[Kit laughs]

1652
01:31:28,875 --> 01:31:30,541
Honestly, that'll probably
be her role forever.

1653
01:31:31,208 --> 01:31:33,666
[clears throat] You know what, Amihan?

1654
01:31:33,750 --> 01:31:37,250
Can you please stop this sad girl shit?

1655
01:31:37,333 --> 01:31:40,916
Hannah and Matteo
are not even married yet.

1656
01:31:41,000 --> 01:31:43,541
If you wanna do something,
you've still got time, right?

1657
01:31:47,625 --> 01:31:48,958
You're right, actually.

1658
01:31:50,000 --> 01:31:51,083
Thanks!

1659
01:31:51,750 --> 01:31:53,416
[Kit] Wait, no, you can't!

1660
01:31:53,500 --> 01:31:56,875
-Stop!
-Why not?

1661
01:31:58,375 --> 01:31:59,958
You're drunk.

1662
01:32:00,041 --> 01:32:01,500
Hey, I'm not drunk.

1663
01:32:02,416 --> 01:32:03,833
[scoffs]

1664
01:32:03,916 --> 01:32:05,791
What are you gonna do? Go to Hannah?

1665
01:32:05,875 --> 01:32:08,041
-Yes!
-And then what?

1666
01:32:08,125 --> 01:32:09,208
You're gonna stop her
from marrying Matteo?

1667
01:32:09,291 --> 01:32:10,333
Yes.

1668
01:32:11,166 --> 01:32:13,208
[scoffs] Are you for real?

1669
01:32:13,291 --> 01:32:17,375
If you do that, what are you
gonna do afterwards?

1670
01:32:18,791 --> 01:32:21,750
I can't deal with that question,
I'm drunk, okay?

1671
01:32:21,833 --> 01:32:24,083
But you just said you're not drunk!

1672
01:32:24,166 --> 01:32:27,291
Okay, fine. Go to Hannah
if that's what you want.

1673
01:32:27,375 --> 01:32:29,416
And what are you gonna offer her?

1674
01:32:30,166 --> 01:32:32,208
What, Mihan?

1675
01:32:32,291 --> 01:32:36,833
You're not beating the "good at the start,
but zero follow-through" allegations.

1676
01:32:37,541 --> 01:32:40,500
-What is your problem?
-What do you mean?

1677
01:32:40,583 --> 01:32:42,375
You're still hung up on
what happened between us?

1678
01:32:43,500 --> 01:32:44,500
[Mihan scoffs]

1679
01:32:45,875 --> 01:32:47,500
Charlie, you're making
a huge deal out of nothing.

1680
01:32:47,583 --> 01:32:49,666
What happened was just
a lapse in judgment!

1681
01:32:49,750 --> 01:32:51,333
And you kissed me first, Charlie.

1682
01:32:52,916 --> 01:32:55,583
[exclaims] Damn it!

1683
01:32:55,666 --> 01:32:58,291
Seriously? Are you for real right now?

1684
01:32:58,375 --> 01:33:00,166
Stop acting like a kid over this!

1685
01:33:00,250 --> 01:33:02,541
You can't just make out alone, you know!

1686
01:33:02,625 --> 01:33:04,291
You were part of it!

1687
01:33:04,375 --> 01:33:06,333
You even drove us to the motel.

1688
01:33:06,416 --> 01:33:08,958
[Kit exclaims]
What do you mean, motel?

1689
01:33:10,500 --> 01:33:11,916
For what?

1690
01:33:13,500 --> 01:33:15,500
Did you guys have sex?

1691
01:33:16,083 --> 01:33:18,750
Why would you do that? When was it?

1692
01:33:19,750 --> 01:33:21,666
I feel like Charlie...

1693
01:33:22,625 --> 01:33:25,291
just wants Hannah to get married
so she can have a shot with me.

1694
01:33:25,375 --> 01:33:27,791
[in English] Oh, wow!

1695
01:33:27,875 --> 01:33:28,916
[in Filipino] I can feel it.

1696
01:33:33,125 --> 01:33:34,458
You know what, Amihan?

1697
01:33:35,041 --> 01:33:36,458
You're so full of it.

1698
01:33:37,500 --> 01:33:38,750
Okay, fine, you're cute.

1699
01:33:39,625 --> 01:33:42,125
You're a National Book Awardee, fine!

1700
01:33:42,208 --> 01:33:43,666
But you're also kind of stupid.

1701
01:33:44,500 --> 01:33:46,666
I've said it over and over.

1702
01:33:46,750 --> 01:33:48,041
Go ahead and marry Hannah.

1703
01:33:48,583 --> 01:33:50,250
You still have time.

1704
01:33:51,125 --> 01:33:54,291
How can I marry her if Kit's stopping me?

1705
01:33:54,375 --> 01:33:56,000
[Kit] Can you two just stop it?

1706
01:33:56,875 --> 01:33:59,166
Mihan, Charlie, why did you do that?

1707
01:34:00,625 --> 01:34:02,625
We're all friends now!

1708
01:34:02,708 --> 01:34:04,791
Haven't you learned your lesson?

1709
01:34:04,875 --> 01:34:07,333
Shouldn't we be done
crossing those lines by now?

1710
01:34:07,416 --> 01:34:09,500
Whoa, Marikit!

1711
01:34:10,125 --> 01:34:12,916
Could you cut that
high-and-mighty act of yours?

1712
01:34:13,000 --> 01:34:15,125
-What?
-You think I don't notice

1713
01:34:15,208 --> 01:34:16,791
you making the moves on me?

1714
01:34:16,875 --> 01:34:19,416
You've got a thing for me, huh?

1715
01:34:19,500 --> 01:34:21,166
Waiting for me to give in?

1716
01:34:21,250 --> 01:34:22,416
Waiting for you?

1717
01:34:23,041 --> 01:34:24,166
What "moves" do you mean?

1718
01:34:24,875 --> 01:34:27,708
You know, if I had feelings for you...

1719
01:34:29,875 --> 01:34:31,125
I don't give in to that.

1720
01:34:32,750 --> 01:34:33,583
Because...

1721
01:34:34,583 --> 01:34:35,625
[scoffs]

1722
01:34:36,500 --> 01:34:37,625
Because what?

1723
01:34:41,500 --> 01:34:43,416
[in English]
Because feelings aren't facts!

1724
01:34:47,750 --> 01:34:49,000
Okay...

1725
01:34:51,083 --> 01:34:52,708
Damn!

1726
01:34:52,791 --> 01:34:53,791
[sighs]

1727
01:35:05,125 --> 01:35:06,125
[grunts]

1728
01:35:07,250 --> 01:35:08,625
Damn it...

1729
01:35:20,000 --> 01:35:21,750
I can't believe you did that.

1730
01:35:26,875 --> 01:35:29,458
Why did you guys give in
to the alcohol so fast?

1731
01:35:32,375 --> 01:35:33,375
[Mihan inhales deeply]

1732
01:35:35,000 --> 01:35:38,666
Your fiancé was the one
who backed down first.

1733
